s head abruptly and pushed past his small servant, into the wardrobe. Kreen stood very still in the lavatory for a few seconds, his grief genuine. Lodovik had always given Kreen the impression that the small Lavrentian was the equal of anybody within thei
r acquaintance. Kreen treasured that evaluation, even though it had never been spoken.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
