Klayus dismissed the women with a few soft words. As they departed, they strolled around the hall, and he bent over to confide to Hari, "They don't impress you, do they? Their kind make up a large portion of the women her
e. Beautiful as frozen moons. My Privy Councilor manages to search out others of higher quality, but... !" He sighed. "Fine stones are easier to procure than gems among females, for a man in my position. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "It was so with Cleon, as well, Highness, " Hari s
aid. "He made arrangements with three princess consorts throughout his youth, then, in his middle years, foreswore women entirely. He died without an heir, as you know. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I've studied Cleon, of course, " the Emperor said thoughtfully. "A solid man, not intelligent, but very capable. He liked you, didn't he?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I doubt any Emperor has ever liked a man such as myself, Highness. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Oh, don't be so modest! You have great charms, really. You were married to that remarkable woman\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Dors Venabili, " said a reedy voice behind them.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The Emperor turned gracefully, his robes swishing over the floor, and his face lit up. "Farad! How nice of you to come early. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The Privy Councilor bowed to his Emperor and glanced in passing at Hari. "When I heard of your visitor, I could not resist, Highness. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You know my Privy Councilor, Farad Sinter, and Farad, this is the famous Hari Seldon. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "We've never met, " Hari said. No one shook hands in the Emperor's company; too many weapons had been transferred}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 between conspirators and assassins in past centuries that way for a simple handshake to be any other than a gross and even dangerous breach of etiquette.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I've heard much about your famous wife, " Sinter said with a smile. "A remarkable woman, as the Emperor says. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Hari has come here to warn me about your activities, " Klayus said with a small grin, glancing between them. "I did not know all you've been up to, Farad. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "We've discussed my goals, Highness. What more does Professor Seldon have to add, in the way of information?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "He says you're hunting down mechanical men. Robots. From what he says, you appear to be obsessed with them. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari stiffened. This was becoming a very dangerous situation, and he was beginning to feel a noose tighten. He almost regretted having taken this di
rect approach with someone so devious and unpredictable as Klayus. It would not be at all good to be singled out and marked for reprisal by Farad Sinter...}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "He's confused my goals, though perhaps the rumors have misled him. There are many false rumors about our activities, Highness. " Sinter's smile dripped honey and bonhomie.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 

\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "This genetic study... most valuable, don't you think, Hari? Has anyone explained it to you?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "System-wide, and also the twelve nearest Central Stars, " Sinter said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "It has been explained in the journals of Imperial Science, " Hari said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "But shooting people!" Klayus continued. "Why, Farad? To take samples?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari could hardly believe what he was hearing. The Emperor could just as easily have signed Hari's death warrant. Instead, he seemed to be handing Hari's head to his Privy Councilor... on a plate, for dinner!}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Those, those are lies of course, " Sinter said slowly, eyes heavy-lidded. "The Emperor's police would have reported such indiscretions. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I wonder, " Klayus said, eyes twinkling merrily. "At any rate, Farad, Raven here has some excellent points to make about this robot search. Hari, explain to us the
 political difficulties that might ensue, should such charges ever become widely disseminated. Tell Farad about\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "fo-jo Joranum, yes, I know, " Sinter said, his lips thinning and his cheeks going white. "A Mycogenian would-be usurper. Stupid and easily manipulated\emdash by you, in part, am I correct, Professor Seldon?"}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "His name was mentioned, " the Emperor said, glancing off to one side as if beginning to be bored.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Actually, " Hari said, "Joranum was just a symptom of a larger myth, with consequences far worse on other worlds than Trantor. " A myth I have not thought about, not measured, not researched\emdash 
all because of Daneel's prohibitions! Even now, Hari realized he would have some difficulty discussing the topic. He coughed into his fist. Sinter offered a hand
kerchief, but Hari shook his head and produced his own. Accepting such an item could also be misconstrued. And would it even be dangerous? Has Trantor and the Empire come to that? Either way, Hari would not fall for such a simple set-up. "On the world of 
Sterrad. Nikolo Pas. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The Emperor stared at Hari blankly. "I'm not familiar with Nikolo Pas. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "A butcher, Highness, " Sinter said. "Responsible for the death of millions. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Billions, actually, " Hari said. "In a vain search for artificial humans he claimed were infiltrating the empire. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The Emperor stared at Hari for several seconds, his face slack. "I should know about him, shouldn't I?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "He died in Rikerian the year before you were born, Highness, " Sinter said. "It is not a glorious moment in Imperial History. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Something in the atmosphere had changed. Klayus had a sour, even a disappointed look, as if he were anticipating an }{\fs20 un}{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 p}{\fs20 l}{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
easant duty Hari glanced sideways at Sin}{\fs20 t}{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 er and saw that}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
