 concern. Then it was that Hari realized Klayus and Sinter had been playing with him. The Emperor already knew about the murders of citizens on Trantor. Yet neither Sinter nor any of his tutors had told him about Nikolo Pas, and this was upsetting him.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I'm not supposed to be so ignorant, " Klayus said. "I really should set up more time for personal study. Go on, Raven. What about Nikolo Pas?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "In decades past, and every few centuries, Highness, there have been tides and even storms of psychological disturbance, centered on the myth of the Eternals. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Sinter visibly flinched. This gave Hari some satisfaction. He continued.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "The resurgence of tha
t myth has almost invariably led to social unrest, and in a few extreme cases, genocide. I conducted an interview with Nikolo Pas when I served Cleon as First Minister, Highness. I spent several days speaking with him, an hour or two at a time, in his cel
l
 deep in Rikerian. " The memories seemed to fill Hari's mind now. "What did Pas believe?" the Emperor asked. The servants were at their positions around the hall. All the arrangements had been completed, the dinner was being delayed; guests could not be a
llowed to enter until the Emperor had left, to make a more formal entrance later. Klayus did not seem concerned by this.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Pas claimed to have captured an active artificial human. He claimed to have placed it... " Hari coughed again. In this context, he coul
d hardly bring himself to use the word robot. He felt badly exposed and even handicapped, for the prohibition against discussion of Daneel's nature had spread to other areas of thought, memory, even will. "He claimed to have isolated the artificial human
\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Robot. We could be here all night, " Klayus said impatiently. That seemed to break some barrier, and Hari nodded.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Robot. In very secure quarters. The robot deactivated itself\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "How frightening, how noble!" Klayus exclaimed.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Pas claimed his scientists 
dissected and analyzed the body. And yet the body, the inactive mechanical form, was removed from these extremely secure circumstances and vanished without a trace. This was the beginning of Nikolo Pas's crusade. The details are far too long and gruesome 
to be spoken of here, Highness, but I'm sure you can locate them in the Imperial Library. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klayus's eyes were like marbles in the head of a wax figure, pointed in Hari's general direction. He rotated toward Sinter. "Your point seems obvious, Hari. Professor Seldon. May I call you Hari?"}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The Emperor had already asked him that at their last meeting, but Hari did not let on. Once again, he replied, "I would be honored, Highness. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "The point being that these waves of misery inevitably begin when some high offi
cial gets a bug in his hat and begins futile investigations. And when the investigations get out of hand, they cost the Empire many lives and much of treasure. Superstitions. Myths. Always dangerous, like religions. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Sinter said nothing. Hari merely nodded. Both had beads of moisture on their foreheads. The Emperor seemed thoughtful and calm.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I'm willing to vouch that my Privy Councilor has no such illusions, Hari. I hope I can reassure you of that. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes, Highness. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
"And you, Farad, you understand the depth of Hari's concern, that he comes here to relay these items of information about the state of bureaucratic and popular perceptions? The citizens! Like a sea of whispers. The Greys! The eternal manipulators of human
 destiny, the greatest power below the Palace! And the gentry\emdash baronial and aristocratic, aloof, conspiratorial... So important and so often subject to fluctuating themes. Eh?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari did not understand quite what the Emperor meant.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "No hard feelings against Hari, eh, Farad?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "None, of course, sire. " Sinter smiled sunnily at Hari.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Still... " Klayus put his chin in one hand and tapped his lips with a finger. "Amazing story! I shall have to look into it. What if the butcher's notions were true? That would change everything. What then?"}{
