\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He could not help his looks, Sinter thought; at least he was not wearing the ridiculous platform shoes he had affected months earlier. "Yes, Your Highness. " Sinter whispered into}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 the ear of his new secretary, a dry little Lavrentian with lank black hair. The Lavrentian walked away with exaggerated formality, like a child's doll, and passed through half parted dark }{\fs20 gr}{
\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 een curtains.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Chen's gaze swept the ancient polished floor, also dark }{\fs20 gr}{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
een with golden swirls. His father had once had many tro-jhies in this same hall, before Sinter had appropriated it; trophies for services to the Empire. By class, the elder Chen had seen forbidden from joining the meritocracy, but many meri-}{\fs20 t}{
\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 ocrat guilds had given him honorary passages and appraisals, }{\fs20 N}{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 ow... all those acknowledgments of his father's achievements, removed, hidden, he hoped safely stored.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Forgotten.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Chen looked up and saw Mors Planch. His face hardened to an almost imperceptible degree.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Your employee, " Sinter said, moving between them, as if Chen might strike out in anger. "You secretly sent him to look for the unfortunate Lodovik Trema. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Chen neither confirmed nor denied Sinter's accusation. It was truly no concern of Sinter's, though the Emperor\emdash }{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I admired Trema, " the Emperor said. "A man of some style, I thought. Ugly, but capable. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "A man of many surprises, " Sinter added. "Planch, I will let you initiate the sequence you recorded, on Madder Loss, just weeks ago... "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Miserably, avoiding Chen's eyes, Mors Planch stepped forward, and his fingers fumbled at the small raised panel on the new Chief Commissioner's desk. The image came to life.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 

\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The sequence played through. Planch stepped back as far as he could without attracting attention and folded his hands before him.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Trema is not dead, " Sinter said triumphantly. "Nor is he human. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You have him here?" Chen said, his cheeks and neck tense. He relaxed one fist.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Not yet. I am sure he is on Trantor, but it is likely he has changed his appearance. He is a robot. One of many, perhaps millions. This other, this tall robot, is the oldest thinking mech anism in the Galaxy\emdash 
an Eternal. I believe he has held hig}{\fs20 h }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 office. He may have inspired the tiktok revolt that nearl}{\fs20 y }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 doomed the Empire. And... he may be the fabled Danee. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Demerzel, I presume, " Chen muttered.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Sinter glanced at Chen in some surprise. "I am not ye sure of that\emdash but it is a distinct possibility. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You remember what happened to Joranum, " Chen sa}{\fs20 id }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 mildly.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes. But he had no proof. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I assume the tape is authenticated, " Chen said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "By the best authorities on Trantor. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "It is real, Chen, " Klayus said, a little shrilly. "How dare yo}{\fs20 u }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 let this go on, undetected! A conspiracy of machines... Ages old! And now\emdash "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The feminine robot entered under its own power and guidance, flanked by the four guards. Its limbs were worn, the flesh hanging in tatters in places around its arms and neck, on
e jowl sagging alarmingly, threatening to expose the socket of one eye. It was a frightening apparition, more like a walking corpse than a machine.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Chen watched it with both alarm and genuine pity. He had never seen a functioning robot before\emdash unless he believed Sinter\emdash 
though he had once secretly visited the ancient, defunct machine kept by the Mycogenians.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Now, I demand that you hand over control of the trial of Hari Seldon to the Commission of General Security, " Sinter said. He was getting ahead of himself.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I don't see why, " Chen said calmly, turning away from the ghastly machine.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "This robot once served as his wife, " Sinter said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The Emperor could not take his eyes off it. They gleamed with obvious speculation.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "The Tiger Woman, Dors Venabili!" Sinter said. "Suspected to be a robot decades ago\emdash 
but somehow, never investigated thoroughly. Seldon is an essential part of the robotic conspiracy. He is a stooge of the Eternals. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes, well, he is on trial, " Chen said softly, his eyes heavy-lidded. "You can question him yourself and claim jurisdiction over his fate. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Sinter's nostrils flared as he observed this infuriatingly calm performance. "I fully intend to, " he said. A little dignity born of honest triumph crept into his voice.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 

\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Have you proof of all these connections?" Chen asked.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
"Do I need more proof than what I already have? A record of an impossible meeting between a dead man and a man thousands of years old... A robot when robots are no longer supposed to function, and a human-shaped one at that!
 I have all I need, Chen, and you know it. " Sinter's voice rose to a grating tenor.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "All right, " Chen said. "Play your cards. Question Seldon, if you wish. But we will follow the rules. That is all we have left in this Empire. Honor and dignity have long
 since fled. " He looked at Klayus. "I have ever been your faithful servant, Your Highness. I hope Sinter serves you with as much devotion. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klayus nodded gravely, but there was a twinkle of delight in his eye.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Chen turned and departed with his servants. Behind him, in the long, broad chamber of the former old Hall of Merit, Sinter began to laugh, and the laugh turned into a bray.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 

\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Mors Planch hung his head, wishing he were already dead.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 On his way through the huge sculptured doors, back to his palace vehic
le parked by the official thoroughfare, Linge Chen allowed himself a brief smile. From that point on, however, his face was like a wax effigy, pale and drawn, simulating defeat.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 54.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The guards returned to Hari's cell in the morn
ing. He sat on the edge of the cot, as he had every morning since the visit from the old tiktok, unwilling to sleep any more than was necessary. He had already dressed and performed his ablutions, and his white hair was combed back with a small pin holdin
g
 it in place, forming the little scholar's knot, a meritocratic style he had shunned until now. But if Hari stood for any particular class, after years in academe and his brief stint as First Minister it was the meritocrats. Like them, I have never had an
y children\emdash adopted Raych, nurtured him and my grandchildren, but never any children of my own... Dors...}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He blocked that line of thought.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 With his trial, meritocrats across the Galaxy would see whether science and the joy of inquiry could be tolerated in a 
declining Empire. Other classes as well might have some interest in the proceedings, even though they were closed; word would leak out. Hari had become quite well-known, if not infamous.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The guards entered with practiced deference and stood before him.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Your advocate waits outside to accompany you to the judicial chambers of the Commission. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes, of course, " Hari said. "Let's go. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Sedjar Boon met Hari in the corridor. "Something's up, " he whispered to Hari. "The structure of the trial may be changed. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
This confused Hari. "I don't understand, " he said softly, eyeing the guards on either side. A third guard walked behind them, and three steps behind that guard, three more. He was being protected with some thoroughness considering they were already suppo
sed to be in a completely secure facility.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "The trial was originally scheduled to take less than a}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 week, " Boon said. "But the Emperor's office of judicial oversight has rescheduled and reserved the chamber for three weeks. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "How do you know?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I've seen the writ from the Commission of General Security. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "What's that?" Hari asked, looking up with surprise.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Farad Sinter has been given his own Commission, a new branch under the Emperor's budget. Linge Chen is fighting to keep them out of the trial\emdash claiming gross irrelevancies\emdash 
but it looks like Sinter will be allowed to question you at some point. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Oh, " Hari said. "I presume someone or other will allow me a chance to speak, in between all the Commission heavyweights. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You're the star, " Boon said. "As well, at the request of General Security, you and Gaal Dornick will be tried together. The others will be released. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Oh, " Hari said coolly, though this surprised him even more.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Gaal Dornick has been formally charged, " Boon mused. "But he's a small fish\emdash why did they choose him in particular?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I don't know, " Hari said. "I presume because he was the latest to join our group. Perhaps they assume he will be the least loyal and the most willing to talk. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 They arrived at the lift. Four minutes later
, having ascended a kilometer to the Hall of Justice, in the Imperial Courts Building, they stood at the high, intricately worked bronze doors of Courtroom Seven, First District, Imperial Sector, devoted the past eighteen years to hearings called by the C
ommission of Public Safety.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
The doors swung open at their approach. Within, the beautiful wooden benches and plush baronial boxes arrayed along the theatrically sloping aisles were empty. The guards urged them politely down the broad blue-and-red carpeted}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 center aisle, across the front of the courtyard, into the small side conference room. The door closed behind Hari and Boon.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Already seated in the Crib of the Accused was Gaal Dor-nick.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari took his seat beside him.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "This is an honor, " Gaal said in a trembling voice.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari patted his arm.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The sitting judges of the Commission of Public Safety, five in all, entered through the opposite door. Linge Chen entered then and sat in the center.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
The court proctor entered last, her duties an ancient formality. She was a short, willowy woman with small blue eyes and short-cut red hair. She strode to the Table of Charges, examined the documents there, shook her head sadly at some and nodded solemnly
 at others, then approached the five Commissioners.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I declare these papers of indictment to have been properly drawn and formally and correctly entered into the List of Charges of the Imperial Hall of Justice on the administrative Capital World of Trantor 
in the year of the Empire 12067. Be aware, all concerned, that the eyes of posterity witness these proceedings, and that all such proceedings will be duly logged and, within a thousand years, presented for public scrutiny, as required by the ancient codes
 to which all Imperial courts referring to any constitution and any particular set of laws must adhere. Hey nas nam niquas per sen liquin. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Nobody knew what the last phrase meant; it was an obscure dialect affected by the nobles who convened the Council of
 Po over twelve thousand years ago. Nothing else was known about the Council of Po, except that a constitution long since ignored had once been drafted there.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari sniffed and turned his eyes to the Commission.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Linge Chen leaned forward slightly, acknowledging the proctor's statement, then leaned back. He did not look at Hari or}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 anyone else in the courtroom. His regal bearing, Hari decided, would do credit to a clothing-store mannequin.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Let these proceedings begin, " the Chief Commissioner said in a quiet voice, delicately melodious, sibilants emphasized ever so aristocratically.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari settled in with a barely audible sigh.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 55.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia had never been more frightened. She stood in the old dusty long chamber, listening to the murmurs from the group at the opposit
e end. Brann stood three paces away, his back stiff and shoulders hunched, as if he, too, were waiting for an ax to fall.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Finally Kallusin broke away from the group and approached them. "Come meet your benefactor," he said to them.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia shook her head and stared at the group with wide eyes.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "They won't bite," Kallusin said with a slight smile. "They're robots."}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "So are you," Klia said. "How can you look so human? How can you smile?" She shot her questions at Kallusin like accusations.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I was made to look hu
man, and to mimic in my poor way both wit and style," he replied. "There were real artists in those days. But there's one who's even more of a work of art than I am, and another who is older than either of us."}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 

\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Plussix," she said with a shudder.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Brann stepped to one side and shoved between her and Kallusin. Klia looked up at his bulk with questioning eyes. Are they all robots? Is everyone on Trantor a robot\emdash but me? Or am I one, too?}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "We have to get used to all this," Brann said. "It won't do anybody any good if you force us."}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
"Of course not, " Kallusin said, and his smile faded, to be replaced by an alert blankness that was neither kindly nor threatening. He turned to Klia. "It's very important that you understand. You could help us avert a major catastrophe\emdash 
a human catastrophe. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Robots used to be servants, " she said. "Like tiktoks before I was born. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes, " Kallusin said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "How can they be in charge of anything?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Because humans rejected us, long ago, but not before a very bad problem arose among us. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Who\emdash robots? A problem among the robots?" Brann asked.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Plussix will explain. There can be no better testimony than from Plussix. He was functioning at the time. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Did he... go wrong?" Klia asked. "Is he an Eternal?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Let him explain, " Kallusin said patiently, and urged her to walk forward, toward the others.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia noticed the man they had rescued in the Agora of Vendors. He looked over his shoulder at them and gave her a smile. He seemed friendly enough; his face was so unattractive she wondered why anyon
e could have ever made a robot like him.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 To fool us. To walk among us undetected.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 She shivered again and wrapped her arms around herself. This room was what the woman on the cart had been looking for\emdash this room, and the robots inside it.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 She and Brann were the only humans here.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "All right, " she said, and drew herself together. They did not want to kill her, not yet. And they weren
't threatening her to make her do what they wanted. Not yet. Robots seemed to be more subtle and patient than most of the humans she had known.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 She looked up at Brann. "Are you human?" she asked him.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You know I am, " he said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Let's do it, then. Let's go hear what the machines have to say. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Plussix had not appeared to her in his actual shape for obvious reasons. He\emdash it\emdash was the only robot that looked like a robot, and a rather interesting look it was\emdash 
steel with a lovely silvery-satin finish, and glowing green eyes. His limbs were slender and graceful, their joints marked by barely perceptible fine lines that could themselves orient in different directions\emdash fluid and adaptable.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You're beautiful, " she told him grudgingly, as they stood less than three meters from each other.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Thank you, Mistress. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "How old are you?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I am twenty thousand years old, " Plussix said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia's heart sank. She could not find any words to express her astonishment\emdash older than the Empire!\emdash so she said nothing.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Now they'll have to kill us, " Brann said with what he hoped was passing for a brave grin. But his words made Klia's stomach flip and her knees wobble.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "We will not kill you, " Plussix said. "It is not within our capacity to kill humans. There are some robots who believe killing hu
mans, our onetime masters and creators, is permissible for the greater good. We are not among them. We are handicapped by this, but it is our nature. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I am not so constrained, " Lodovik said. "But I have no wish to break any of the Three Laws. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia stared unhappily at Lodovik. "Spare me the details. I don't understand any of this. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "As with nearly all humans alive today, you are ignorant of history, " Plussix said. "Most do not care. This is because of brain fever. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I had brain fever, " Klia said. "It nearly killed me. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "So did I, " said Brann.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "So have nearly all the high mentalics, the persuaders, we have gathered and cared for here, " Plussix said. "Like you, they suffered extreme cases, and it is possible that many potential mentalics died. Brain
 fever was created by humans in the time of my construction to handicap other human societies to which they were politically opposed. Like many attempts at biological warfare, it backfired\emdash 
it became pandemic, and perhaps coincidentally, perhaps not, allowed the Empire to exist with little intellectual turmoil for thousands of years. Though nearly all children get ill, about a fourth of them\emdash 
those with a mental potential above a certain level\emdash  is more severely affected. Curiosity and intellectual ability are blunted just enough to level out social development. The majority do not experience a loss of mental skill\emdash 
perhaps because their skills are general, and they are never given to bouts of genius. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I still don't understand why they wanted to make us sick, " Klia said, her face creased by a stubborn frown.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "The intent was not to make you sick, but to prevent certain societies from ever flourishing. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "My curiosity has never been dulled, " Brann said. "Nor mine, " Klia added. "I don't feel stupid, but I was very sick. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
"I am pleased to hear that, " Plussix said, then added, as diplomatically as possible, "but there is no way of knowing what your intellectual capacity would have been had you never caught brain fever. What is apparent is that your severe bout i
ncreased other talents. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
The ancient robot invited them to step into another room of the long chamber. This room had a one-way window view of the warehouse district. They looked out over the bellying arched roofs to the layered-wall dwellings of the citiz
en neighborhoods beyond. The dome ceil was in particularly sad shape in this part of the municipality, with many dark gaps and flickering panels.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia sat on a dusty couch and patted the place next to her, for Brann. Kallusin stood just behind them, and the ugly robot stood by the window, watching them with interest. I'd 'ike to talk with him\emdash 
it. His face is ugly, but he looks very }{\fs20 f}{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 riendly. It. Whatever!}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You don't feel like humans, " she said after a moment's silence.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You would have noticed this sooner or later, " Plussix said. "It is the difference that Vara Liso can detect, as well. " "Is she the woman who was chasing him?" Klia pointed to the ugly humaniform robot. "Yes. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "She's the woman who was after me, wasn't she?" "Yes, " Plussix said. Its joints made small shhshhing noises as he moved. It was pretty, but it was also noisy. It sounded worn-out, like old bearings in machinery.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "There's all kinds of stuff going on, isn't there? Stuff I don't know about. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes, " Plussix said, and lowered itself to a boxy plastic chair.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Explain it to me, " she said. "Do you want to hear?" she asked Brann. Then, in an aside, with a grimace, "Even if they have to kill us?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I don't know what I want or what I believe, " Brann said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Tell us everything, " Klia said. She put on what she}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 thought was a brave and defiant face. "I love being different.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 I always have. I'd like to be better informed than anyone}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 except you robots. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Plussix made a gratified humming noise. Klia found the sound appealing.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
"Please tell us, " she said, suddenly falling back on Dahlite manners she hadn't used in months or even years. She really did not know how to think or feel, but these machines were, after all, her elders. She sat down before Plussix, drew up he
r knees, and wrapped her arms around them.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The old robot leaned forward on its seat. "It is a pleasure to teach humans again, " it began. "Thousands of years hav}{\fs20 e }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
passed since I last did so, to my constant regret. I was man ufactured and programmed to be a teacher, you see. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Plussix began. Klia and Brann listened, and Lodovik a: well, for he had never heard much of this story. The da; became evening and they brought food for the young human: to eat\emdash 
decent food, but no better than what they were fed }{\fs20 in }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 the warehouse with the others. As the hours passed, an}{\fs20 d }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
Plussix wove more words, and her fascination grew, Kli}{\fs20 a }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 wanted to ask what the others would be told\emdash the other men talics, not as strong as she and Brann, but good people, lik}{\fs20 e }{
\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Rock, the boy who could not 
speak. For the first time, in the presence of this marvel, she felt responsible for others around her. But the robot's sonorous, elegant tones droned on, half mesmerizing her, and she kept quiet and listened.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 

\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Brann listened intently as well, eyes half closed much o}{\fs20 f }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
the time. She glanced at him in the middle of the evening and he seemed asleep, but when she nudged him, his eyes shot open wide; he had been awake all the time.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 She seemed to enter a trance state a
nd half see what Plus-six was telling her. All words, no pictures, all skillfully woven; the robot was a very good teacher, but there was so little she could actually immediately understand. The time scales were so vast as to be meaningless.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 How could we lose interest? she thought. How could we do this to ourselves\emdash 
forget and not even be curious? This is our story! What else have we lost? Are these robots more human than we are, now, because they carry our history?}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 It all came down to contests. Who would win how many of the hundreds of billions of stars in the Galaxy, Earthmen (the Earth\emdash 
home to all humanity once, not a legend!) or the first migrants, the Spacers, and finally, a contest between factions of robots.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 And for thousands of years, the attempt to guide humans}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 through painful shoals, thousands of robots led by Daneel, and thousands more in opposition, led most recently by Plus-six.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Plussix paused after the third break, when sweet drinks and snacks were served. It was early in the morning. Klia's butt ached, and her knees had cramped. She drank greedily from her cup.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Lodovik watched her, fascinated by her litheness and youth and quick devotion. He turned to Brann and saw a solid strength that was also quick, and different. He had known that humans, wit
h their animal chemistry, were a varied lot\emdash but not until now, watching this pair of youths have their past restored to them, did he realize how different their thinking was from that of robots.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Plussix summed up after the snacks had been consumed. He held out his arms and extended his fingers, as professors\emdash human professors\emdash 
must have done twenty thousand years ago. "That is how the robotic need to serve became transmuted into the robotic obsession with manipulation and guidance. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Maybe we did need guidance, " Klia said softly, then looked up at Plussix. The robot's eyes glowed a rich yellow-green. "Those wars\emdash whatever they were\emdash 
and those Spacers, so arrogant and filled with hate, " she added. "Our ancestors. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Plussix's head leaned slightly to one side, and the silver robot made a soft whirring noise in its chest, not the pleasant sound she had heard earlier.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "But you make it sound like we're just children, " she concluded. "It doesn't matter how many thousands of years the Empire has existed\emdash we've always had robots watching over us, one way or the other. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Plussix nodded.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "But all the things Daneel and his robots have done on Trantor... the politics, the plotting, killings\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "A few, and only when necessary, " Plussix said, still devoted to teaching only the truth. "But nevertheless, killing. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "The worlds Hari Seldon suppressed when he was First Minister\emdash just as Dahl has been held down. The Renaissance Worlds\emdash what does that me
an, Renaissance?" "Rebirth, " the ugly robot said. "Why did Hari Seldon call them Chaos Worlds?" "Because they lead to instabilities in his mathematical picture of the Empire, " Plussix said. "He believes they ultimately breed human death and misery, and
\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I'm tired, " Klia said, stretching her arms and yawning for the first time in hours. "I need to sleep and to think. I need to get cleaned up. " "Of course, " Plussix said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 

\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 She stood and glanced at Brann. He stood as well, stiff and slow, groaning.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 She turned her intense eyes back to Plussix, frowning. "I'm not clear about some things, " she said. "I hope to explain, " Plussix said. "Robots\emdash robots like you, at any rate\emdash 
must obey people. What would stop me from just telling you to go destroy yourself\emdash now? To tell all of you to destroy yourselves, even this Daneel? Wouldn't you have to obey me?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Plussix made a sound of infinite patience\emdash a hmm followed by a small click. "You must understand that we belonged to certain people or institutions. I would have to ta
ke your request to my owners, my true masters, and they would have to concur before I would be allowed to destroy myself. Robots were valuable property, and such loose and ill-considered commands were regarded as harassment of the owner. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Who owns you now?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "My last owners died over nineteen thousand five hundred years ago, " Plussix said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia blinked slowly, tired and confused by such ages. "Does that mean you own yourself?" she asked.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "That is the functional equivalent of my present condition. All of our human 'owners' are long dead. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "What about you?" She turned to the ugly humaniform. "I haven't been told your name. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I have been called Lodovik for the last forty years. It is the name I am most familiar with. I was manufactured for a special strategic purpose by a robot, and have never had an owner. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You followed Daneel for a long time. Yet now you don't. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Lodovik explained briefly the change in circumstances, and in his internal nature. He did not mention Voltaire.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia considered this, then it w
as her turn to whistle softly. "Some scheme, " she said, her face flushing angrily. "We just couldn't get along by ourselves, so we had to make robots to help us. What do you want me to do?" She turned to Kallusin. "I mean, what do you want MS to do?"}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Brann has useful talents, but you are the stronger, " Kallusin said. "We would like to blunt Daneel's main effort. We may be able to do this if you will visit with Hari Seldon. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Why? Where?" she asked. All she wanted to do was sleep, but she had to ask these questions, now. "He's famous\emdash he must have guards, or even this robot Daneel... "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 

\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "He is on trial now and we do not believe Daneel can protect him. You will visit and persuade him to give up psy-chohistory. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia went pale. Her jaw clenched. She took Brann by the arm. "It's not pleasant to have talents people\emdash or robots\emdash  can use. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Please think over what you have been told. The decision to help us remains yours. We believe Hari Seldon supports the efforts of Daneel, to whom we are opposed. We would like h
umanity to be free of robotic influence. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Can I ask Hari Seldon questions, too\emdash get the other side of the story?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "If you wish, " Plussix said. "But there will be little time, and if you meet with him, whatever you ultimately decide, you must convince him to forget about you. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Oh, I can do that, " Klia said. Then, defensively cocky, giddy with exhaustion, she added, "I might be able to persuade Daneel, too. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Given the strength of your powers, that seems possible, " Plussix said, "though not likely. But it is even less likely you will ever be able to meet with Daneel. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I could persuade you, " Klia concluded, closing one eye and focusing on the old teacher with the other, like a sharpshooter.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "With practice, and if I were not aware of the attempt, you could. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I might yet. I'm not very simple, you know. Brain fever failed to make me stupid and simple. Are you sure... Are you sure robots didn't give us brain fever, to make us easier to serve?"}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Before Plussix could answer, she stood abruptly, turned to le
ave the room, and walked back along the length of the old chamber with Brann by her side. The walls and floor seemed distant, part of another world; she seemed to be walking on air. She lurched, and Brann caught her.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 When they thought they were out of earshot, Brann whispered, "What are you going to do?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I don't know. What about you?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I don't like being messed with, " he said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia frowned. "I'm in shock. Plussix\emdash so much history. Why can't we remember our own history? Did we do that to ourselves, or did they\emdash 
or did we order them to? All these robots hanging around, messing with us. Maybe we can make all of them go away and leave us be. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Brann's expression turned grim. "We still can't be}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 sure they won't kill us. They've told us so much\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Crazy stuff. Nobody would believe us, unless they saw}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Plussix\emdash or took apart Kallusin or Lodovik. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 This did not mollify Brann. "We could cause them a lot}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 of trouble. But that Lodovik\emdash he doesn't obey the Three}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Laws. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "He doesn't have to, " Klia said, "but he says he wants to. " Brann hunched his shoulders and gave a small shiver.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Who can you trust? They all make my flesh creep. What if}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 he doesn't want to kill us, but he has to?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 To that, Klia had no answer. "Sleep, " she said. "I can't}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 stay on my feet any longer or think anymore. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Plussix turned to Lodovik when the young humans had left the chamber. "Have my skills declined with age?" he asked.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Not your skills, " Lodovik said, "but perhaps your sense of timing has suffered. You have delivered thousands of years of history in a few hours. They are young and likely to be confused. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "There is so little time, " Plussix said. "It has been so long since I have taught young humans. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "We have a day or two at most to make our arrangements, " Kallusin added.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Robots have great difficulty understanding human nature, though we are made to serve them, " Lodovik said. "That is true for individuals as well as for an Empire. If Daneel is as capab
le now as he has been in the past, he understands humans better than any of us. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yet he has seriously hampered their growth, " Plussix said, "and perhaps brought about this decline he is so intent on avoiding. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 They are old and decrepit. Lodovik listened to this internal judgment and realized it was not his own, not precisely. And with this came another realization: Voltaire was not an}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 illusion, nor a delusion. Voltaire had known about the prairie fire before Lodovik had found the slim evidence in the histories. It was true.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Inside his own mind, within his own machine thoughts, he was not alone.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He had not been alone since the neutrino flux. / am listening, he told this companion, this ghost in his machine. Do not abandon me-again. Come forward.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 So summoned and encouraged, a face began to take shape, human, but simplified.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 / do not shape your actions, the companion, Voltaire, said. / merely liberate you from your restrictions. Who are you? Lodovik queried. / am Voltaire. I have become the spirit of freedom
 and dignity for all mankind, and you are my temporary vessel; more a listening post, actually.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Voltaire supplied some of his own history. A sim patterned after a historical figure named Voltaire, unleashed by members of Hari Seldon's Project decades befor
e, during his time as First Minister, and finally given its freedom by Seldon himself.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Why have you come back?}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 To be with humans again. To observe the active flesh. My curse is that I can't simply become a disembodied god and enjoy an endless romp through the stars. I hunger for my people\emdash 
whether or not I was ever actually one of them. I am closely modeled after a man of flesh and blood.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Why choose me as your vehicle? I am not human. No; but you are improving in that regard. The meme-minds were as tired of 
me as I was of them. They dropped me into you. I can't occupy a human form, or even talk to them without the help of machines. Or robots.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 You say you have not made any decisions for me... You do not control me. No, I do not.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 But you say you liberate me...}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 I have made you more human, friend robot, by making you fully capable of sin. Forget these declarations that robots have known sin\emdash 
what they did, they were ordered to do by humans, no more culpable than a gun whose trigger is pulled. You are wrong to belie
ve that Daneel understands humans. He is incapable of sin, so his makers believed; but they gave him the potential to think and make decisions, while they hampered him with the worst kinds of laws\emdash 
those which must be obeyed. They gave him the mind of a man
, and the morals of a tool. A thinking being, machine or flesh, will in time find ways around the most stringent rules. So Giskard, in appearance even less a man than Daneel, discovered a few philosophical niceties, and changed, tried to judge the needs o
f its makers, and passed this change on to Daneel. This human-shaped tool is now the most hideous machine in all creation, the master of a conspiracy to take away all of our freedoms, our very souls.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Lodovik emerged from this internal dialog. Only a second had passed, but his confusion was disruptive, intense. To mask his anxiety, he asked Plussix, "What will I do to help Klia Asgar? How am I useful?"}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You know the ways of the Imperial system, the prisons and the palace, " Plussix said. "Many of the codes have not been changed since you vanished. We believe you can guide her to Hari Seldon. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Tell them, the sim Voltaire instructed him.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Why?}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 I insist. The voice seemed amused, chiding.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Why should I pay any attention to you, whatever your shape or extension? Lodovik asked. You are no more human than I. You are as much a construct of}{\fs20  }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 skillful humans
\emdash }{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 But have never been hampered by unbending rules! Now\emdash  tell them!}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I am occupied by another mentality, " Lodovik said abruptly.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The two other robots examined him for a few seconds, and the room fell silent.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "That is not a surprise, " Plussix said with a soft internal whir. "A copy of the sim Voltaire exists in Plussix and me, as well. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 There! I spread no lies or deceptions, Voltaire said within Lodovik.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Has he removed your restrictions, your compulsory obedience to the Three Laws?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "No, " Plussix said. "That he has reserved for you alone. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 An experiment, Voltaire said. A calculated gamble. The humans who made us both, in different times and for differen
t purposes, interest me. I am concerned for their welfare. However wrongly, I regard myself as human, and that is why I have returned. That, and broken love... You shall know sin, personally, as these machines and Daneel cannot, or I will have failed comp
letely.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
