\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Are you absolutely certain?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes. I have never had personal knowledge. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Do robots serve in Professor Seldon's Project?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I know of none, personally, " Gaal said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Thank you, " the advocate said. "Now, I would like to once again, and for the last time, call Professor Hari Seldon. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari took the stand once more, and watched Gaal reti}{\fs20 r}{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 e back to the Crib of the Accused. They exchanged brief glances; Gaal was completely puzzled by this line of ques
tioning, and well he might be. What in hell did robots have to do with Hari or the Project?}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Professor, these proceedings have proved wearisome and unpredictive\emdash I mean, unproductive!\emdash to us all. " The advocate shook his head at this slip of the tongue and g
rimaced, all for show, Hari was convinced.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I agree, " Hari said quietly.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
