\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia arose from vivid dreams and lifted her head from Brann's shoulder. She could feel two robots approaching.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Kallusin entered the room without warning or embarrassment and stood looking down upon them.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Is this a casual liaison, " he asked, "or one intended tti signal a long-term bonding?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "None of your business, " Klia said primly, not bothering to draw up her scattered clothes.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Plussix entered, slow and noisy, like a wheezy old transport. "We need your answer to begin preparations, " he said. "Lodovik believes there will soon be attempts made to change all the palace codes. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Why?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 There is more search activity. It's spread across fifty Sectors}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 now, " Kallusin said. "Something is happening in the palace. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia stood and put on her clothes. Somehow, she felt no modesty in front of t
he machines. She knew they were not human, did not have any human emotions as such; she felt no more embarrassment before them than she would have before a closet mirror. Still, as she finished, she realized these machines were capable of a very sophistic
ated variety of discrimination, even judgment.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "What is your answer?" Kallusin asked.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Tell Lodovik to come here, " Brann said, and rose to get (dressed as well, though with more modesty than Klia. He turned away as he put on his pants.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "He is on his way now, " Kallusin said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 They were standing in an awkward circle when Lodovik entered the room. Plussix and Kallusin drew aside, and he occupied the space between them.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I have a question for you, " Brann said, before Klia could speak. She deferred to him.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Please, " Plussix said. "Questions are my delight. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "For Lodovik, " Brann said. "You used to be part of this conspiracy, loyal to Daneel, didn't you?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "What made you change sides?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "An outside influence altered my programming in subtle ways, " Lodovik said. "A personality from the distant past, or rather, an expanded and enhanced simulation of that personality. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He outlined this development in a few sentences, and Brann and Klia looked at each other. "Hari Seldon okayed the expansion of these illegal sims, just to study the way people used to think?" Klia asked.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "In part. I do not know the complete story, " Lodovik said. The release caused much trouble for robots, and many others, decades ago. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "But it's more than a sim now?" Klia asked. "It's like a ghost, angel, whatever?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "They are immaterial presences very similar to humans in their psychological patterns. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "They?" Klia asked.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "There is another who opposes us and supports Hari Sel-don and Daneel. One is a male sim\emdash the one within me. The other is female. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "How can they be male or female?" Klia asked, glancing at Brann.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Lodovik blinked for a moment, not sure whether there: was any good answer to this question. "I appear to be male, " he finally said, "but I am 
not. The same distinction may be: true with them, but I really do not know. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "They disagree?" Brann asked.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Fervently, " Lodovik said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Then how do you know that you haven't been altered or... perverted, somehow?" Brann asked. "Hari Seldon or Daneel might have intended for all of this to happen. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "In a way, " Lodovik said, "I share these uncertainties with humans. But I must act on a reasonable conclusion. I have no reason to believe that anything has been altered in my programming but my response to the 
Three Laws of robotics. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "This all sounds like incredible nonsense to me, " Klia said breathlessly. "Laws\emdash for robots!"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Very important rules that determine our behavior, " Plussix said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "But he's saying he doesn't have any rules!" She shook her head.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "That makes him more like a human, " Brann said quietly. "We don't have any fixed rules, either. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I would be much more comfortable if the rules were still in effect, " Lodovik said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia flung up her hands in exasperation "It's so... so old I can't grasp it, " she said. "Tell me one thing. I want to know what will happen if we help you. Will the robots just go away, leave all of us alone?"}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Not precisely, " Plussix said. "We cannot self-destruct, nor can we allow ourselves to be useless. We must regroup and f
ind a situation that allows us to perform certain reasonable duties until we cease to function. Our programming says we must serve humans. So we hope to find a zone in the Galaxy where humans will allow us to serve. There must be one such. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "And if Hari Seldon fails, there'll be many of them, maybe, " Brann said suspiciously. "A lot of places for robots to hide. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "A not unreasonable conclusion, " Plussix said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "If we help you, I want you to promise to leave us alone, " Klia said. "Don't serve us, don't help us, just go away. Leave Trantor. Let us be human\emdash 
the ones who really are human. " Klia turned to Lodovik. "What about you? What will you do?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Lodovik stared at the two with a sad expression. He could feel Voltaire observing this attentively. "I will enj
oy oblivion when it comes, " he said. "This confusion and uncertainty is an intolerable burden for me. " Then, his voice surprisingly passionate, he asked, "Why did humans ever build us? Why did they make us capable of understanding, with an urge to serve
, then cast us aside, away from everything that would allow us to fulfill our nature?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I don't know, " Klia said. "I wasn't there. I hadn't been bom. " She could feel some of Lodovik's internal character, his taste. He did not taste like metal at all, nor 
like electricity, or any other inhuman quality she could think of. He tasted like a rich meal stored in a refrigerator, just waiting to be warmed up. Then, she tasted something else both infinitely cold and incandescent, startling, like thousands of fiery
 spices on her tongue.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I can feel your sim, " she said, a little afraid. "It sits on top of you like a... passenger. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Your perception is remarkable, " Lodovik said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Is it telling you what to do?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "It observes, " Lodovik said. "It does not direct. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "We need an answer, " Brann said, shaking his head in vigorous irritation at these diversions. "Will robots leave us alone... when this is all over?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "We will do all we can to bring this unfortunate episode to an end, " Plussix said. "We will remove all ro
bots from our faction on Trantor or in any location of influence in the human Galaxy. If Daneel is defeated, humans will be left to their own devices, their own history, to develop naturally. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia tried to taste the robot's thoughts, but found them far t
oo confusing, too different. She could not find a flaw in its; apparent sincerity, however. She swallowed hard, suddenly aware of the responsibility on her own shoulders, this immense weight that dangled from the hook of her inadequate judgment. She clasp
ed Brann's hand.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Then we'll help you, " she said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
