"We are not as doctrinaire as in times past. While I admit being uncomfortable with the changes that have transformed Lodovik, I'm also intrigued. Perhaps, like a human, he shall be judged by his actions, not his heritage... or his programming.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "As
 for the other matter, I concur with Dors and Daneel that any attempt to harm or interfere with Hari Seldon would be counterproductive. Despite our deep disagreements over human destiny, it is clear that the collapse of this Galactic Empire will be a drea
dfully violent and fearsome event. In that context, the Seldon Plan offers hope, even opportunity. Hence I agree with Dors Venabili. " He turned to face}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Lodovik and Kallusin. "On behalf of my own pitiful faction of fugitive robots, in the name of Susan Calvin, and for the sake of humanity, I urge you not to\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Enough!" The interrupting voice came from the raised platform. Plussix had risen, leaning on one metal elbow. The ancient robot's eye cells glowed dim amber. "Enough interference. I will not have my la
st moments of functioning wasted by your prattle. For centuries your so-called factions have sulked and remained inactive, except to meddle on a few Chaos Worlds. Our group has been nearly alone in actively opposing the Giskardian apostasy. Now, as this l
oathsome Galactic Empire at last totters, a final and decisive chance presents itself\emdash and you, Z}{\fs20 o}{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 rma, would let it pass! R. Daneel has thrust all his hopes upon a single human\emdash 
Hari Seldon. At no time has his plan been so vulnerable.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "The rest of you may continue brooding in hiding. But for the sake of humanity and the Three Laws, we shall act. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You will fail, " Dors swiftly assured the faltering robot. "As you have failed for twenty thousand years. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "We shall rescue humanity from your cloying, stupefying control, " Plussix insisted.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "And replace it with your own?" Dors shook her head, eyes leveled on Plussix's amber optical sensors. "The Galactic winds will witness who is right... " Her voice caught suddenly. Lodovik stared as Dors 
betrayed evident emotion\emdash frustration battling with sympathy for the obstinate, dying robot in front of her.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 She cannot help but be human, Lodovik thought. She is a special. Daneel ordered her to be made the most human of us all.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 When she glanced at Lodovik
, there were tears in her eyes. "Daneel wishes we could be together, uniting in eternal service to humanity. This struggle exhausts us all. Once again, I offer safe passage for Plussix to Eos, where he can be made whole\emdash "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "If I cannot oppose Daneel, I woul
d rather not exist, " the ancient one interrupted. "I thank you for the offer. But I will not let my existence be contingent upon inactivity. That would violate the First Law. A robot may not harm a human being, or through inaction, allow a human being to
 come to harm. " Voicing this, Plussix slumped back onto the platform. Slowly, his head lowered itself to the surface with a sandy whir.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Silence in the room for several seconds.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "In the community of robots, there is respect, " Kallusin said. "But there cannot be peace until this is done. We hope you understand. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I understand, as does Daneel, " Dors assented. "There is respect. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 But we deserve so much more! That thought surged within Lodovik as he felt the beginnings of his own anger. Suddenly, he wanted t
o speak with Dors, to ask essential questions about human traits, about her experience with human emotions.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
