\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 If the cry of a child could have been made of knives, it could not have cut Klia any more deeply than the mentalic shock wave surrounding Vara Liso.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Disappointment, grief, anger, an intense sense of misplaced justice, images of people long dead\emdash parents, young friends, who had disappointed this small woman with the knotted face and crab-curled fists\emdash 
batted against Klia, fragments of ruin in a flood of pain.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
The walls and pillars and panes of the Hall of Dispensation felt nothing. Vara Liso's output was tuned to a purely human channel, to the roots of mind in matter. Because she had not focused her talents completely on him, Lodovik felt merely a buzzing and 
a pressure not dissimilar to the neutrino flux he had encountered between the stars.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He did, however, sense what Daneel saw very clearly\emdash the disintegration of the entity who had spoken in him and through him. Voltaire stood in simple nakedness before this 
flux, this human tempest, and broke apart like a child's puzzle.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 For a moment, Klia's sympathetic response nearly allowed her to die, to both drown and be burned by the outpouring. She felt the echoes of her own life, her own experiences, mesh with those of Vara Liso.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
