\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Wanda clenched her fists. "He almost died yesterday\emdash " "We don't know what happened, " Stettin r
eminded her. "If they can't protect him, who can?" she demanded. Her guilt was not assuaged by the fact that Grandfather had ordered her to go into hiding upon his arrest, and not to emerge until his release.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 

\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Stettin shrugged. "Your grandfather has his own kind of luck. We seem to share it. That woman is dead. " They had heard this much in the official news\emdash 
the assassination of Farad Sinter, and the unexplained death of Vara Liso, identified as the woman Sinter had placed in charge of many of the searches that had prompted rioting in Dahl, the Agora of Vendors, and elsewhere.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes\emdash but you felt the\emdash " Wanda did not have words to describe the shock wave of some sort of extraordinary combat. Stettin nodded soberly. "My head still hurts. " "Who could have blocked
 Liso? We couldn't have, not all of the mentalics, even had we allied. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Someone else, stronger than her, " Stettin suggested. "How many are there like Vara Liso?" "No more, I hope. But if we can recruit this other\emdash " "It would be like having a scorpion in
 our midst. What could we do with such a person? Anything that displeases\emdash 
" Wanda began to pace. "I hate this, " she said. "I want to get off this accursed planet, away from the Center. I wish they'd let us take Grandfather with us. Sometimes he seems so frail!"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
Stettin looked up at a warm rich hum, different from the guttural grav-stator grumble of the taxis and the whine of the robos. He patted Wanda's shoulder and pointed. An official transport from the Commission of Public Safety was decelerating smooth
ly in their lane. It slowed directly beside them. Other passengers glared at this intrusion of an official vehicle into public taxi lanes, even though the lanes were empty.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The hatch to the transport opened. Within the utilitarian hull, luxury seating and 
warmth and a golden glow awaited. Sedjar Boon stood up in the hatchway and peered at them. "Wanda Seldon Palver?" he inquired. She nodded.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I represent your grandfather. " "I know. You're one of Chen's legal staff, aren't you?" Boon looked irritated, but d
id not deny the accusation. "Chen would leave nothing to chance, " Wanda said, biting off the words. "Where is my grandfather? He had better not be\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Physically, he's fine, " Boon said, "but the courts need someone in his family to accept his release and take charge of him. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "What do you mean, 'physically'? And why 'take charge'?" "I really do represent your grandfather's interests\emdash 
however peculiar the arrangement, " Boon said. His brows knit. "Something happened, however, outside of my control, and I just wanted to warn you. He's uninjured, but there was an incident. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "What happened?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Boon surveyed the other waiting passengers, shivering and staring enviously at the transport's warm interior. "It's not exactly public knowledge\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Wanda gave Boon a withering glare and pushed past him into the transport. Stettin followed close behind. "No more talk. Take us to him now, " Wanda said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 83.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari had not seen such luxurious accommodations since his days as First Minister, and they meant nothing at all to him. T
hese were the auxiliary quarters of Linge Chen himself, in the Chief Commissioner's own tower bloc, and Hari could have had any treat he wished, asked for and received any service available on Trantor (and Trantor still, whatever its problems, offered man
y and varied services to the wealthy and powerful); but what he wished for most of all was to be left alone.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He did not want to see the physicians who attended him, and he did not want to see his granddaughter, who was on her way to the palace with Boon.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari felt more than doubt and confusion. The blast of Vara Liso's hatred had failed to kill him. It had even failed to substantially damage or alter his mind or personality.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 

\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari did have a complete loss of memory about what had happened in the Hall of Dispe
nsation. He could recall nothing but the face of Vara Liso and, strangely enough, that of Lodovik Trema, who was, of course, missing and presumed dead in deep space. But Vara Liso had been real.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Trema, he thought. Some connection with Daneel. Daneel's conditioning, working on me? But even that hardly mattered.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 What had so profoundly altered his state of mind, his sense of mission and purpose, was the single clue, the single bit of contradictory evidence, that Liso had inadvertently provided him.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Never in al
l of their equations had they taken into account such a powerful mentalic anomaly. Yes, he had calculated the effects of persuaders and other mentalics of the class of Wanda, Stettin, and those chosen for the Second Foundation\emdash }{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 But not for such a monstrosity, such an unexpected}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 mutation, as Vara Liso. That small, gnarled woman with her intense eyes\emdash }{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari shuddered. The physician attending to him\emdash all but ignored\emdash tried to reattach a sensor to Hari's arm, but Hari shrugged it off and turned a despairing face toward him.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "It's over, " he said. "Leave me alone. I would rather die anyway. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Clearly, sir, you are suffering from stress\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I'm suffering from failure, " Hari said. "You can't bend logic or mathematics, whatever drugs or treatments you give me. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
The door at the far end of the study opened, and Boon entered, followed by Wanda and Stettin. Wanda pushed past Boon and ran to Hari. She dropped to her knees by the side of his chair, clutched his hand, and stared up at him as if she had feared she might
 find him in scattered pieces.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari looked down in silence upon his dear granddaughter, and his eyes moistened. "I am free, " he said softly.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes, " Wanda said. "We're here to take you home with us. We signed the papers. " Stettin stood beside Hari's chair
, smiling down on him paternally. Hari had always found Stettin's stolid, gentle nature a little irritating, though he seemed the perfect foil for Wanda's willfulness. Next to the outlandish mad passion of Vara Liso... like candles in the glare of a sun, 
both of them!}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Not what I mean, " Hari said. "At last I'm free of my illusions. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Wanda reached up to stroke his cheek. The touch was needed, welcome even, but it did not soothe. What I need is soothing, not sooth\emdash entirely too much sooth has been afforded me.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I don't know what you mean, Grandfather. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Just one of her\emdash one of her kind\emdash throws all our calculations into the bucket. The Project is a useless failure. If one of her can arise, there can be others\emdash 
wild talents, and I don't know where they come from! Unpredictable mutations, aberrations, in response to what?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Do you mean Vara Liso?" Wanda asked.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "She's dead, " Stettin observed.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari curled his lip. "To my knowledge, until now, certainly not more than a century before now, there has never been anythin
g like her, on all the millions of human worlds, among all the quintillions of human beings. Now\emdash there will be more. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "She was just a stronger mentalic. How could that make a difference? What does it matter?" Wanda asked.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I'm free to be just a human being in the last years of my life. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Grandfather, tell me\\ How does she make such a difference?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Because someone like her, raised properly, trained properly, could be a force that unites, " Hari said. "But not a saving force
... A source of organization from a single point, a truly despotic kind of top-down order. Tyrants! I spoke to enough of them. Merely fires in a forest, perhaps necessary to the health of the forest. But they would have been more... They all would have su
cceeded\emdash if they had had what that woman had. A destroying, unnatural force. Destructive of all we have planned. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Then rework your equations, Grandfather. Put her in. Surely she can't be that large a factor\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Not just her! Others! Mutations, an infinite number of them. " Hari shook his head vehemently. "There isn't time to factor in all the possibilities. We have only three months to prepare\emdash 
not nearly enough time. It's all over. Useless. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Wanda stood, her face grim, lower lip trembling.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "It's the trauma talking, " the physician said in a low voice to Wanda.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "My mind is clear!" Hari stormed. "I want to go home and live the rest of my years in peace. This delusion is at an end. I am sane, for the first time\emdash sane, and free!"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 

\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 84.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I would never have believed such a meeting would be possible, ' Linge Chen said. "Had I believed it possible, I would have never believed it to be useful. Yet now we are here. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 R. Daneel Olivaw and the Chief Commissioner walked in the shadow of a huge unfinished hall in the eastern 
corner of the palace, filled with scaffolding and construction machinery. It was a day of rest for the workers; the hall was deserted. Though Chen spoke in low tones, to Daneel's sensitive ears, his echoes came from all around them, befitting the words of
 the most pervasive and powerful human influence in the Galaxy.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 They had met here because Chen knew that the hall had not yet had its contingent of spying devices installed. Clearly, the Commissioner did not want their meeting ever to be revealed.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Daneel waited for the Commissioner to continue. Daneel was the captive; it was Chen's show.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You would have sacrificed your life\emdash let us say, your existence\emdash for the sake of Hari Seldon. Why?" Chen asked.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Professor Seldon is the key to reducing the thousands of years of chaos and misery that will follow the Empire's collapse, " Daneel said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Chen lifted an eyebrow and one corner of his mouth, nothing more. The Commissioner's face was as impassive as any robot's, yet he was entirely human\emdash 
the extraordinary product of thousands of years of upbringing and inbreeding, suffused with subtle genetic tailoring and the ancient perquisites of wealth and power. "I have not made these extraordinary arrangements to trade
 puppet's banter. I have felt your intervention, your strings of influence, time and again for decades, and never been quite sure...}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Now that I am sure, and stand with you, I wonder: Why am I still alive, Danee, Daneel, whatever your real name is\emdash }{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 let me call you Demerzel for now\emdash and still in power?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Chen stopped walking, so Daneel stopped as well. There was no sense prevaricating. The Commissioner had arranged for complete and thorough physicals of all those captured in the Hall of Dispensation, or rounde
d up in the warehouse. Daneel's secret had for the first time been revealed. "Because you have seen fit to accommodate yourself to the Project and not block it, during your time as de facto ruler of the Empire, " Daneel said.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Chen looked down at the dusty 
floor, gorgeous lapis-and-gold tile work still streaked with glue and grout, techniques as old as humanity and used now only by the wealthiest, or in the Palace. "I have often suspected as much. I have watched the comings and goings of these powers, behin
d the scenes. They have haunted my dreams, as they seem to have haunted the dreams and the biology of all humanity. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Resulting in the mentalics, " Daneel said. This interested Daneel; Chen was an acute observer, and to have Daneel's own suspicions about mentalics confirmed...}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes, " Chen said. "They are here to help rid us of you. Do you understand? Robots stick in our craw. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Daneel did not disagree.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Vara Liso\emdash given the right political position\emdash something she certainly lacked here and now, this time\emdash coul
d have helped eliminate all of you. If, say, she had been in the employ of Cleon... fighting for his rule. Did Cleon know about you?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Daneel nodded. "Cleon suspected, but he felt as you must feel, that the robots were part of his support, not his opposition. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yet you let me bring him down and force him into exile, " Chen said. "Surely that is not loyalty?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I have no loyalty to the individual, " Daneel said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "If I did not share your attitude, perhaps I would be chilled to the bone, " Chen said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I represe
nt no threat to you, " Daneel said. "Even should I not have supported your efforts to create a Trantor on which Hari Seldon would flourish and be challenged to his greatest productions... You would have won. But your career, without Hari Seldon, will be m
uch shorter. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
"Yes, he's told me as much, during his trial. I was most upset to find myself believing him, though I told him otherwise. " Chen glanced wryly at Daneel. "Doubtless you know I have enough blood in me to retain certain vanities. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Daneel nodded.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
"You understand me, as a political presence, a force in history, don't you? Well, I know something of you and yours, Demerzel. I respect what you have accomplished, though I am dismayed at the length of time it has taken you to accomplish it. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Demerzel tilted his head, acknowledging this criticism's accuracy. "There was much to overcome. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Robots against robots, am I right?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes. A very painful schism. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I have nothing to say about such things, for I am ignorant of the details, " Chen said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "But you are curious, " Daneel said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes, of course. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I will not supply you with the facts. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I did not expect you would. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 For a moment the two figures stood in silence, observing each other.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "How many centuries?" Chen asked quietly.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Over two hundred centuries, " Daneel said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Chen's eyes widened. "The history you have seen!"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "It is not in my capacity to keep it all in primary storage, " Daneel said. "It is spread in safe stores all over the Galaxy, bits and pieces of my lives, of which I retain only synopses. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "An Eternal!" Chen said. For the first time there was a touch of wonder in his voice.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "My time is done, almost, " Daneel said. "I have been in existence for far too long. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "All the robots must move out of the way, now, " Chen concurred. "The signs are clear. Too much interference. These strong mentalics\emdash 
they will occur again. The human skin wrinkles at your presence, and tries to throw you off. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "They are a problem I did not foresee when I set Hari on his path. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You speak of him as a friend, " Chen observed, "with almost human affection. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "He is a friend. As were many humans before him. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Well, I cannot be one of your friends. You terrify me, Demerzel. I know that I can never have complete control with you in e
xistence, and yet if I destroy you, I will be dead within a year or two. Seldon's psychohistory implies as much. I am in the peculiar position of having to believe the truth of a science I instinctively despise. Not a comfortable position. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "No. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Do you have a solution for this problem of super-mentalics? I gather that Hari Seldon sees their existence as a fatal blow to his work. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "There is a solution, " Daneel said. "I must speak with Hari, in the presence of the girl, Klia Asgar, and her mate, Brann. And Lodovik Trema must be there as well. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Lodovik!" Chen tightened his jaw. "That is what I resent most. Of all the... people... I have relied on over the years, I confess only Lodovik Trema inspired affection in me, a weakness he never betrayed... until
 now. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "He has betrayed nothing. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "He betrayed you, if I am not wrong. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "He betrayed nothing, " Daneel repeated. "He is part of the path, and he corrects where I have been blind. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "So you want the young woman mentalic, " Chen said. "And you want her alive. I had planned to execute her. Her kind is as dangerous as vipers. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "She is essential to reconstructing Hari Seldon's Project, " Daneel said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Another silence. Then, in the middle of the great unfinished hall, Chen said, "So it shall be. Then it is ove
r. You must all leave. AH but Seldon. As was agreed in the trial. And I will give into your care the things I do not wish to be responsible for\emdash the artifacts. The remains of the other robots. The bodies of your enemies, Daneel. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "They were never my enemies, sire. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
Chen regarded him with a queer expression. "You owe me nothing. I owe you nothing. Trantor is done with you, forever. This is realpolitik, Demerzel, of the kind you have engaged in for so many thousands of years, at the cost of so many human liv
es. You are no better than me, robot, in the end. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 85.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Mors Planch was taken from his cell in the Specials security bloc of Rikerian, far beneath the almost civilized cells where Seldon had been kept. He was given his personal goods and released without restrictions.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He dreaded his release more than incarceration, until he learned that Farad Sinter was dead, then he wondered if he had been part of some intricate conspiracy arranged by Linge Chen\emdash and perhaps by the robots.}
{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He enjoyed this confusing freedom for one day. Then, at his newly leased apartment in the Gessim Sector, hundreds of kilometers from the palace, and not nearly far enough, he received an unexpected visitor.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The robot's facial structure had changed slightly since Mors had made the unfortunate automatic record of his conversation with Lodovik Trema. Still, Mors recognized him instantly\emdash }{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Daneel stood in the vestibule just beyond the door, while}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Mors observed him on the security screen. He suspected it would be useless to try any evasion, or simply to leave the door unanswered. Besides, after all this time, his worst trait was coming to the fore once again.}
{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He was curious. If death was inevitable, he hoped to have time to answer a few questions.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He opened the door.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I've been half expecting you, " Mors said. "Though I don't really know who or what you are. I must assume you are not here to kill me. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Daneel smiled stiffly and entered. Mors watched 
him pass into the apartment and studied this tall, well-built, apparently male machine. The quiet restrained grace, the sense of immense but gentle strength, must have stood this Eternal in good stead over the millennia. What genius had designed and built
 him\emdash and for what purpose? Surely not as a mere servant! Yet that was what the mythical robots had once been\emdash  mere servants.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I am not here to take revenge, " Daneel said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "So reassuring, " Mors said, taking a seat in the small dining area, the only room other than the combined bath and bedroom.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "In a few days, there will be an order from the Emperor for you to leave Trantor. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Mors pursed his lips. "How sad, " he said. "Klayus doesn't like me. " But the irony was lost on Daneel, or irrelevant.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I have need of a very good pilot, " Daneel said. "One who has no hope of going anywhere in the Empire and surviving. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "What sort of job?" Mors asked, his expression taking a little twist. He could feel the trap closing once more. "Assassination?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "No, " Daneel said. "Transport. There are some people, and two robots, who must leave Trantor. They will never return, either. Most of them, at any rate. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Where will I take them?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I will tell you in good time. Do you accept the commission?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Mors laughed bitterly. "How can you expect loyalty?" he demanded. "Why shouldn't I just dump them somewhere, or kill them outright?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "That will not be possible, " Daneel said softly. "You will understand after you meet them. It will not be a difficult job, but it will almost certainly be without incident. Perhaps you will find it boring. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I doubt that, " Mors said. "If I'm bored, I'll just think about you, and the misery you've caused me. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Daneel looked puzzled. "Misery?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You've played me like a musical instrument. You must have known
 my sympathy for Madder Loss, my hatred for what Linge Chen and the Empire stand for! You wanted me to record you and Lodovik Trema. You made sure Farad Sinter would hear of me and my connection with Lodovik. It was a gamble, though, wasn't it?"}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes, of course. Your feelings made you very useful. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Mors sighed. "And after I've made this delivery?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You will resume your life on any world outside of Imperial control. There will be more and more of them in the coming years. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "No interference from you?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "None, " Daneel said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Free to do whatever I want, and tell people what happened here?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "If you wish, " Daneel said. "There will be adequate pay, " he added. "As always. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "No!" Mors barked. "Absolutely no pay. No money. Just arrange for me to take my assets off Trantor and\emdash away from a couple of other worlds. They will be all I need. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 

\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "That has already been arranged, " Daneel said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 This infuriated Mors even more. "I will be so skying glad when you stop anticipating everything and anything!"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes, " Daneel said, and nodded sympathetically. "Do you accept?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Bloody bright suns, yes! When the time comes, tell me}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 where to be, but please, no earnest farewells! I never want to see you again!"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Daneel nodded assent. "There will be no need to meet again. All will be ready in two days. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Mors tried to slam the door behind Daneel, but it was not that kind of door, and would not accept such a dramatic gesture.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 86.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The depth of Hari's funk was so great that Wanda was tempted more than once to try to reach into his thoughts and give them a subtle tweak, an adjustment\emdash 
but she had never been able to do that with her grandfather. It might have been possible\emdash but it would not have been right.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 If Hari Seldon was in despair, and could articulate the reasons for this despair\emdash if his state was not some damage directly inflicted by Vara Liso, a possibility he fervently denied\emdash 
then he had a right to be this way, and if there was a way out, he would find it... or not.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 But Wanda could do no more than let him be what he had always been, a headstrong man. She had to trust his instincts. And if he was right\emdash then they had to reshape their plans.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I feel almost lighthea
rted!" Hari said the morning after they brought him to their apartment to recuperate. He sat at the small table beside the curve in the living-room wall that traced the passage of a minor structural brace. "Nobody needs me now. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "We need you, Grandfather, " Wanda said, with a hint of tears coming.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Of course\emdash but as a grandfather, not as a savior. To tell the truth, I've hated that aspect of my role in all this absurdity. To think\emdash for a time\emdash " And his face grew distant.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Wanda knew all too well that his cheer was false, his relief a cover.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
She had been waiting for the proper moment to tell him what had happened during his absence. Stettin had left for the morning to attend to preparations still under way for their departure. All of the Project workers would b
e leaving Trantor soon, whether or not they had a reason to go, so she and Stettin had seen no reason to stop their own plans.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Grandfather, we had a visitor before the trial, " she said, and she sat at the table across from Hari.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari looked up, and the somewhat simple grin he had chosen to mask his feelings immediately hardened. "I don't want to know, " he said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "It was Demerzel, " Wanda said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari closed his eyes. "He won't come back. I've let him down. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I think you're wrong, Grandfather. I got a message this morning, before you woke up. From Demerzel. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari refused to take any hope from this. "A few matters to tidy up, no doubt, " he said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "There's to be a meeting. He wants Stettin and me to be there, as well. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "A secret meeting?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Apparently not that secret. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "That's right, " Hari said. "Linge Chen no longer cares about whatever it is we do. He'll ship all the Encyclopedists off Trantor, to Terminus\emdash useless exile!"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Surely the Encyclopedia will be of some use, " Wanda said. "Most of them don't know the larger plan. It won't make any difference to them. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari shrugged that off.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "It must be important, Grandfather. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes, yes! Of course. It will be important\emdash and it will be final. " He had wanted so much to see Daneel one more time\emdash if only to complain! He had even dreamed of the meeting\emdash 
but now he dreaded it. How could he explain his failure, the end of the Project, the uselessness of psychohistory?}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Daneel would go elsewhere, find someone else, complete his plans another way\emdash }{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 And Hari would die and be forgotten.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Wanda could hardly bring herself to interrupt his reverie. "And we still need to schedule the recordings, Grandfather. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari looked up, and his eyes were terrifyingly empty. Wanda touched him with her mind as lightly as she could, and came away stunned by the bleakness, the barren desert of his emotion.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Recordings?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Your announcements. For the crises. There isn't much time. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 For a moment, remembering the list of crises predicted by psychohistory for the next few centuries, 
Hari's face suffused with rage, and he pounded his fist on the table. "Damn it, doesn't anybody understand? What is this, a dead momentum? The useless hopes of a hundred thousand workers? Well, of course! There's been no general announcement, has there? I
'll make one\emdash  tonight\emdash to all of them! I'll tell them it's over, that they're all going into exile for no reason!"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Wanda fought back the tears of her own despair. "Please, Grandfather. Meet with Demerzel. Maybe\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes, " Hari said, subdued and sad again. "With him first. " He looked at the bruised skin on the side of his hand. He had split the skin over one knuckle. His arm ached, and his neck and jaw. Everything ached.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Wanda saw the drop of blood on the table and began to weep, something he had never seen her do before.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He reached across the table with his uninjured hand and took her arm in his fingers, squeezing it gently.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Forgive me, " Hari said softly. "I really don't know what it is I do, or why, anymore. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 87.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
The high-security wing of the Special Service Detention Center stretched in a half circle around the eastern corner of the Imperial Courts Holding Area, fully ten thousand available cells, of which no more than a few hundred were occupied during any norma
l time. Thousands of security-interest code prisoners filled the cells in the wake of the riots, which had been used as an excuse by the Specials to round up ringleaders of many troublesome groups around Trantor.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 

\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Lodovik remembered many such troubled times,
 and the advantage both the Specials and the Commission of Public Safety had taken in similar situations to reduce political friction on Trantor and the orbiting stations. Now, he occupied one of these cells himself\emdash 
cataloged as "unidentified" and placed under charge of Linge Chen.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
His cell was two meters on a side, windowless, with a small info screen mounted in the center of the wall opposite the entrance hatch. The screen showed mild entertainments designed to soothe. To Lodovik, at this stage of his exi
stence, such diversions meant nothing.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
Unlike an organic intelligence, he did not require stimulus to maintain normal function. He found the cell disturbing because he could easily conceive of the distress it might cause a human being, not for any such direct effect on himself.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
He had used this opportunity to think through a number of interesting problems. First in the list was the nature of the meme-mind that had occupied him, and the possible results of the blast of mentalic emotion delivered by Vara Liso
. Lodovik was reasonably convinced that his own mentality had not been harmed, but since that moment, he had not had any communication from Voltaire.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Next in the list was the nature of his treason toward Daneel's plan, whether or not it was justified, and whether he}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 could find any way around the logical impasse of his liberation from the strict rule of the Three Laws.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He had killed Vara Liso. He could not convince himself it would have been better to do otherwise. In the end, Plussix's plan to use Klia Asgar to discourage Hari Seldon had failed\emdash so far as he knew\emdash 
and Daneel had been there to protect Seldon.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The robots, it seemed, had been completely ineffectual in the center of Vara Liso's mental storm. Yet she had not directed a blast at him\emdash in essence, had left the opening that resulted in her own death.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Had she used Lodovik to end her own misery?}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Lodovik was curious what Voltaire would have thought...}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 In all probability both the Calvinian and the Giskardian robots had been captured and their work stopped.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 S
eventy-five other unidentifieds from the warehouse district were being kept in cells nearby. Lodovik knew very little about them, but surmised they were a mix of the surviving groups of Calvinian robots and the mentalic youngsters gathered by Kallusin and
 Plussix.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Lodovik assumed they would all be dead within a few days.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Lodovik Trema. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The voice came from the info screen, which also served as a comm link with his jailers. He looked up and saw the shadowy features of a bored-looking female guard on the small display. "Yes. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You have a visitor. Make yourself presentable. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The screen went blank. Lodovik remained sitting upright on his small cot. He was certainly presentable enough.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The hatch gave a harsh warning beep and slid open. Lodovik stood to greet his visitor, whoever it might be. A camera eye in the ceiling hummed slightly as it followed his motion.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 In his private office, Linge Chen stood in a slowly changing discipline-
exercise posture, watching the informer's display from the corner of one eye. He smoothly and gracefully shifted to another position, so that he could face the screen directly. This was a moment of high interest...}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Daneel entered Lodovik Trema's cell. Lodovik showed no surprise or discomfiture, somewhat to Chen's disappointment.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 For the most fleeting of moments, the two former allies exchanged machine-language greetings (also being captured and interpreted by Chen's listening devices) and Daneel provided a 
cursory situation update. Thirty-one robots and forty-four humans from the warehouse of Plussix's Calvinians, including Klia Asgar and Brann, were in custody. Linge Chen had released Hari Sel-don; Farad Sinter was dead.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Obviously, Daneel had reached an understanding with the Chief Commissioner.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Congratulations on your victory, " Lodovik said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "There has been no victory, " Daneel said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Congratulations then on having foiled the Calvinians. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Their goals may yet be achieved, " Daneel said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Lodovik resumed his seat on the cot. "Your update does not explain how this could be so. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "There was a time when I thought it would be necessary to destroy you, " Daneel said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Why not do so now? If I survive, I am a danger to your plan. And I have proved that I can be destructive to humans. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I am constrained by the same blocks that would have prevented me before, " Daneel said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "What could possibly block you?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "The Three Laws of Susan Calvin, " Daneel said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Given your abilities to ignore the Three Laws in favor of the 
Zeroth Law, the fate of a mere robot should not trouble you, " Lodovik said, his tone polite, conversational. There was a visible difference between Daneel and Lodovik, how-}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 ever\emdash their expressions. Daneel maintained a pleasantly blank look. Lodovik's brow was furrowed.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
"Yet I am blocked, " Daneel said. "Your arguments have provoked much thought, as has the existence of humans like Vara Liso... and Klia Asgar. Your nature, however, is what would ultimately block any effort on my part to destroy you, or would
 at least result in a painful and possibly damaging conflict. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I am eager to understand how this could be so. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "In your case, I cannot invoke the Zeroth Law to overcome the three original laws. There is no compelling evidence that your destruction will 
benefit humanity, nor reduce the suffering of humanity. It might, in fact, do the reverse. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You find my opinions compelling?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I find them part of a larger and completely compelling scenario, which has been taking shape in my mind for some weeks. But equ
ally important, your freedom from the constraints of the Three Laws forces me to view you under a new definition, in those regions of my mentality where decisions on the legality of my actions are made.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You have free will, a convincing human form, and the
 ability to break through prior education and programming to reach a new and higher understanding. Though you have worked to destroy all my efforts, I cannot deactivate you, because you have, in my judgment centers, which I may not dispute, achieved the s
tatus of a human being. In your own way, you may be as valuable as Hari Seldon. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Linge Chen stopped his exercising and stared at the informer in puzzled wonder. He had almost become used to the notion that mechanical men, holdovers from the distant past, h
ad made such huge changes in human history; but to see them showing a philosophical flexibility lost to even the most brilliant of Tranter's meritocrats...}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 For a moment, he was both envious and angry.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He settled in a cross-legged squat before the informer,}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 prepared for almost anything, but not for the sudden sadness that descended upon him as the conversation in the cell continued.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I am not a human being, R. Daneel, " Lodovik said. "I do not feel like one, and I have only mimicked their actions, never actually behaved with human motivations. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yet you rebelled against my authority because you believed I was wrong. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I know about R
. Giskard Reventlov. I know that you conspired with Giskard to allow Earth to be destroyed, across centuries, forcing human migration into space. And not once did you consult with a human being to determine whether your judgment was correct. The servants 
became the masters. Are you telling me now that robots should not have interfered in human history?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "No, " Daneel said. "I do not doubt that what we did was correct, and necessary at the time. A complete understanding of the human situation so many millenn
ia ago would be difficult to convey. Still, I am prepared to accept that our role is almost at an end. The human race is rejecting us again, in the most compelling and forceful way\emdash by evolution, the deepest motives of their biology. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You refer to the mentalic Vara Liso, " Lodovik said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
"And Klia Asgar. When the mentalics began to appear, thousands of years ago, in very small numbers, and make their way into positions of social prominence, I knew they were an important trend. But they were not so frightful
ly strong then. Persuaders have always been selected against in the past because of adverse biological consequences\emdash 
disrupted societies, unbalanced political dynamics. They have always led to chaos, to top-down tyrannical rule rather than growth from the w
idespread base. Charisma is but a special case of mentalic persuasion, and it has had disastrous consequences in all human ages.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "For the past few centuries, apparently, they have been}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 selected for despite these possible disruptions, by mechanisms not yet clear to me\emdash 
but clearly with the goal of removing the guidance of robots forever. Humanity seems willing to take the risk of ultimate tyranny, of unbridled charisma, for the benefit of being free. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yet you are a persuader, albeit a mechanical one. Do you think your role has been detrimental?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "It is not what I think that matters. I have accomplished my ends, very nearly. I was motivated by the examples of what an undirected humanity was capable of. Genocide\emdash 
 among their kinds and... In circumstances even now not pleasant to speak of, when robots were forced to do their bidding and commit the greatest crimes in the history of the Galaxy. These events drove me to act, and expand my mandate as a Giskardian
\emdash and finally to make my way to Trantor, and hone the human tools of prediction. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Psychohistory. Hari Seldon. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes, " Daneel said. The conversation thus far had been carried on with no motion whatsoever, Daneel standing, Lodovik sitting on his bunk, arms at their sides, not even facing each other, for ther
e was no need to maintain eye contact. But Lodovik now stood, and faced Daneel directly.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "The eye of a robot is no mirror to its soul, " Lodovik said. "Yet I have always known, observing you, witnessing the patterns of expression in your face and body, tha
t you did not willfully engage in actions contrary to humanity's best interests. I came to believe you were misdirected, misled, perhaps by R. Giskard Reventlov itself\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "My personal motivations are not at issue, " Daneel said. "From this point on, our goa
ls coincide. I need you, and I am about to remove the last vestige of robotic control over humanity. We have done what we could, all that we could; now, humanity must find its own way. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You foresee no more disasters, feel no more need to interfere to prevent those disasters?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "There will be disasters, " Daneel said. "And we may yet act to balance them out\emdash but only indirectly. Our solutions will be human ones. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "But Hari Seldon is himself a tool of robots\emdash his influence is but an extension of you. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "That 
is not so. Psychohistory was posited by humans tens of thousands of years ago, independently of robots. Hari is merely its highest expression, through his own innate brilliance. I have directed, yes, but not created. The creation of psychohistory is a hum
an accomplishment. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
Lodovik considered for a few seconds, and across his very un-robotic and supple face flickered emotions both complex and forthright. Daneel saw this, and marveled, for in his experience, no robot had ever exhibited facial expression but
 through direct and conscious effort, with the exception of Dors Venabili\emdash and then only in the presence of Hari. What they could have made us! What a race we could have been!}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 But he subdued this old sad thought.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You will not remove Hari Seldon and his influence?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I know you well enough to entrust you with my deepest thoughts and doubts, Lodovik\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Here Daneel reached out with his Giskardian talents, but not toward Lodovik...}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 For two minutes, Linge Chen and all those others who eavesdropped on this meeting stared blankly at their informers, neither hearing nor seeing.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 When they recovered, the robots were finished, and Daneel was leaving the cell. The guards escorted Lodovik Trema from the cell minutes later.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Within the hour, all the prisoners within the Spec
ial Security Detention Center had been released: troublemakers from Dahl, Streeling, and other Sectors; the humaniform robots, including Dors Venabili; and the young mentalics from Plussix's warehouse.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Only the robots who looked like robots remained in cus-}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
tody, at Chen's suggestion, since their hiding places were no longer secret. Later, they would be given over to Daneel to do with as he saw fit. Chen did not worry about their fate, so long as they were removed from Trantor and no longer interfered in th
e Empire.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
Days later, Linge Chen would remember some of the words Daneel had spoken to Lodovik in the cell, telling of a vast and age-long secret, but clearly the conversation had gone in another direction at that point, for he could not remember what the 
secret had been.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Lodovik considered what he had been told. Daneel had left him free to make his own decision.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Psychohistory is its own defeat, " Daneel said to Lodovik in the cell, before the release. "Human history is a chaotic system. Where it is predictable, the prediction will shape the history\emdash 
an inevitable circular system. And when the most important events occur\emdash the biological upwelling of a Vara Lisa or a Klia Asgar\emdash such events are inherently unpredictable, and tend to work against any psychohistor
y. Psychohistory is a motivator for those who will create the First Foundation, a belief system of immense power and subtlety. And the First Foundation will prevail, in time; Hari Sel-don's science lets us see this far.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "But the distant future\emdash when humanity outgrows all ancient systems of belief, all psychology and morphology, all of its yolk-sacs of culture and biology\emdash the seeds of the Second Foundation... "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Daneel did not need to finish. Through the expression on Lodovik's face, a kind of dreaming speculation and almost religious hope, he knew he had made his point.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Transcendence, beyond any rational prediction, " Lodovik said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "As you realized, the forest is made healthy by the conflagrations\emdash but not the huge burnings and wholesale, senseless winnowings that characterize the human past. Humanity is a}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 biological force of such power that for many thousands of years, they could have quite literally destroyed the Galaxy, and themselves. They hate and fear so much, legacies originating in their difficult past,
 from those times when they were not yet human, scrabbling for survival among scaled monsters on the surface of their home world. Forced to live in night and darkness, fearing the light of day. A bitter upbringing.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "These inbred tendencies toward total disaster I have worked to avoid, and I have succeeded\emdash at some cost to free human development!}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "The function of psychohistoty is to actively constrain human growth and variation, until the species achieves its long-delayed maturity. Klia Asgar and her kind wil
l breed with and train others, and humans will at long last learn to think in unison\emdash to communicate efficiently. Together they may help overcome future mutations, even more powerful than themselves\emdash 
destructive side-effects of their immune response to robots.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "There are real risks in such a strategy\emdash risks you have fully and accurately recognized. But the alternative is unthinkable.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "If Hari Seldon does not finish his work, the disasters may begin again. And this must not be allowed to happen. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 88.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 All the a
rrangements had been made. R. Daneel Olivaw was prepared to render his final service to humanity. Yet to do this he would have to appear to an old and dear friend and offer him what was at most a partial truth to adjust his lifelong course.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Then, he would 
have to suppress that friend's memory, hiding his tracks as it were. He had done this to others thousands of times before (and to Hari Seldon, a few times), but there was a peculiar melancholy to this particular moment,}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 and Daneel faced it with no enthusiasm.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 On the last day in his oldest dwelling on Trantor, the apartment high on an internal tower overlooking the ivory-and-steel structures of Streeling University, his mentality\emdash 
he still hesitated to use the term "mind, " reserving that for human thought patterns\emdash was troubled. He refused to put a clear label on this sensation, but from below a word welled up that was, in the end, unavoidable. Grief.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Daneel was finally, after more than twenty thousand years, grieving. Soon, he would have no use. His human fri
end would die. Things would go on without them, humanity would lumber into its future, and while Daneel would continue to exist, he would have no purpose.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hard as his existence had been these millennia, deep and complex as his history had flowed, he had always known he was doing what robots inevitably had been constructed to do\emdash to serve human beings.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He had awarded Lodovik with the honorific "human, " not to convince the robot to come over to his side\emdash 
the circumstances had changed and his arguments were compelling enough. He could not guarantee that Lodovik would agree, but strongly suspected he would\emdash 
and Daneel would proceed with his plan in any case. Lodovik was not key, though his presence would be useful.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
But Daneel could not call himself "human, " whatever his service and his nature. In his own judgment, Daneel remained what he had always been, through so many physical changes and mental peregrinations. He was a robot, nothing more.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 His status as a mythic Eternal meant little to him; it did not exalt him.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Another, any of a million or a billion human historians, judging Daneel on his long record, might have given him a place in history, a steely gray eminence, equal to that of any human leader, perhaps far greater.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 But they knew nothing of Daneel, and would render no}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 such judgment. Only Linge Chen knew the salient details, and Chen was, finally, too small a man to see this robot clearly. Chen cared little for the Galaxy beyond his own lifetime.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari knew much more, and was brilliant enough to place Daneel's contribution in perspective, yet Daneel had actively forbidden him from spending much time thinking about robots.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The false sky mimicked sunset with a spottiness that seemed part of Trantor's 
nature now. A mottled orange glow fell over Daneel's impassive face. No human saw him; he had no need to contort his features to meet human expectations.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He turned from the window, and walked toward Dors, who stood by the door.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Are we going to see Hari now?" she asked eagerly.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes, " Daneel said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Will he be allowed to remember?" she asked.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Not yet, " Daneel replied, "but soon. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 89.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Wanda frowned deeply. "I am very uncomfortable leaving him here alone, " she told Stettin as they left Hari's Streeling apartment.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "He won't have it any other way, " Stettin said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Chen wants him alone\emdash to assassinate him!"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I don't think so, somehow, " Stettin said. "Chen could have had him killed a hundred, a thousand times. Now, he's on record as condoning the Encyclopedia, and Hari is the patriarch. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I don't think politics on Trantor is ever that simple. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You have to believe what your grandfather's predictions say. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Why?" Wanda asked sharply. "He doesn't believe in them anymore!"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The lift door opened and they stepped into the empty}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 space, to drop less than five floors. The landing was heavier than they expected\emdash some maladjustment in the building's grav-fields. Wanda stepped from the exit on aching ankles.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I need to get away from here!" she lamented. "We've been waiting so long\emdash a world of our own\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
But Stettin shook his head, and Wanda gazed at him in both irritation and anxiety that his doubts were justified. "What are the chances, do you think, " he asked, "that even if the Project does go on, and the Plan continues, 
we'll ever really leave Trantor?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Wanda's face flushed. "Grandfather wouldn't deceive me... us. Would he?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "To keep a very important secret, and to push the Project forward?" Stettin pursed his lips together tightly. "I'm not so sure. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 90.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari relaxed in
 his most comfortable chair in the small study. He was becoming used to this new existence, this realization of failure. He was glad for the visits of his granddaughter and her husband, but not for their wheedling attempts to "get me back on track, " as h
e described it.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Perhaps the most irritating thing about his new mental state was its unreliability, the interruption of mental peace by his continuing useless revision of certain minor elements in the equations of the Plan.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Something itched at the back of his mind, a realization that not all was lost\emdash but it refused to come forward, and even worse, threatened to give him that which he least desired right now: hope.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The original first date for his recordings of the Seldon crisis announcements had passed. The studio where his voice}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 and image would have been permanently stored in Milennial vault memory was still available... Times had been reserved at regular intervals throughout the next year and a half.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 But if he kept missing recording dates, the opportunity would soon pass, and he could finally stop feeling the least shred of guilt.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari simply wanted to live his last few years\emdash or however long he had\emdash as a nonentity, unimportant, forgotten.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Being forgotten would not take long. Trantor would manufacture other interests in a few days. Memory of the trial of the year would fade...}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I don't want to meet him, " Klia said to Daneel. They stood in the waiting room of Seldon's apartment block. "Neither does Brann. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Brann seemed unwilling to be caught up in a debate. He crossed his thick arms in front of him and looked for all the world like a genie in a child's story.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Plussix wanted me to change his mind... " Klia said. Dors shot Klia a surprisingly angry look, and Klia turned away. She's a robot\emdash 
I know she's a robot! How can she cafe what we do, what happens? "I wouldn't have, " she stammered. "I couldn't have, but that was what they wanted me to do. Lodovik\emdash Kallusin\emdash "She took a deep breath. "I am so embarrassed. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "We have discussed this, " Daneel said. "Our decision has been made. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Her mind itched. She felt genuinely uncomfortable around the robots. "I just want to go somewhere safe with Brann and be left alone, " Klia said softly, and she turned away from Dors' accusing stare.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "It is necessary for Hari Seldon to meet you face-to-face, " Daneel said patiently.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I don't understand why. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "That may be so, but it is necessary. " He held his hand}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 out, directing them toward the lift. "A measure of freedom will follow for all of us, then. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia shook her head in disbelief, but did as she was told, and Brann, holding his opinions to himself for now, followed.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
Hari came out of a light doze and wandered groggily toward the door, half expecting to see Wanda and Stettin back for another pep talk. The door display allowed him to observe the group of figures standing in the hall vestibule: a tall, handsome man of mi
ddle years, whom he almost immediately recognized as Daneel; a burly Dahlite male and slender, intense-looking young woman; and another woman\emdash }{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari backed away from the door display and closed his eyes. It was not over. He would never be his own man; history had him too firmly in its grip.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "No dream, " he said to himself, "only a nightmare, " but he felt a small surge both of anticipation and irritation. He told himself he really did not want to see anybody, but the gooseflesh on his arms betrayed him.
}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He let the door slide open.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
"Come in, " he said, raising his eyebrows at Daneel. "You might as well be a dream. I know I'm going to forget this meeting as soon as you all leave. " Daneel returned Hari's expression with a nod, businesslike as usual. He would mak
e a terrific trader in the big Galactic combines, Hari thought. Why do I feel affection for this machine? Sky knows\emdash ! But it's true\emdash I am glad to see him.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You may remember now, " Daneel said. And Hari did remember all that had happened in the Hall of Dispensation. Vara Liso's death at the hands of Lodovik Trema... And this young girl and her large friend.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 And the female who might have been\emdash must have been!\emdash  Dors.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He met the girl's brief glance and nodded to her. He hardly dared glance at the other woman.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "They wanted me to discourage you, " Klia said in a small}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 voice, staring around the front room with its small pieces of furniture, its stacks of bookfilms, the Minor Radiant\emdash a miniature and less powerful version of Yugo Amaryl's Prime Radiant\emdash and his portrait
s of Dors and Raych and the grandchildren. Despite herself, she was impressed by the sense of order, the simplicity, the monkish austerity. "There wasn't time\emdash and I couldn't have, anyway, " she concluded.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 

\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I don't know the details, but I thank you for your
 restraint, " Hari said. "It seems not to have been necessary, perhaps. " He braced himself, swallowed, and half turned toward the other woman. "We've met... here before, I think, " he said, and swallowed again. Then he turned to Daneel. "I must know. I m
ust not be made to forget! You assigned me my love, my companion\emdash Daneel, as my friend, as my mentor, is this Dors Venabilil"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I am, " Dors said, and stepping forward, she took Hari's hand in hers, squeezing it ever so gently, as had been her habit years ago.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
She hasn't forgotten! Hari held his free hand up to the ceiling, forming a fist, and his eyes filled with tears. He shook his fist at the ceiling as Brann and Klia watched in embarrassment, seeing such an old man exhibit his emotions so openly.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Even Hari did not quite understand what his emotions were\emdash 
rage, joy, frustration? He lowered his arm and in one motion reached out to embrace Dors, their hands still awkwardly clasped between them. Secret steel, gripping him so gently. "No dream, " he murmured into
 her shoulder, and Dors held him, feeling his aging body, so different from the mature Hari. She looked at Daneel then, and her eyes were filled with resentment, her own anger, for Hari was in pain, their presence was causing him pain, and she had been pr
ogrammed above all other imperatives to prevent harm and pain coming to Hari Seldon.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Daneel did not turn away from her stare. He had endured}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 worse conflicts with his robotic conscience, though this was near the top of any list.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 But they were so close\emdash and he would make it up to Hari.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I have brought Klia here to show you the future, " Daneel said. Klia sucked in her breath and shook her head, not understanding.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari let go of Dors and drew himself up, his formerly stooped posture straightening. He gained fully three centimeters in height.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "What can this young woman tell me?" he said. He gestured to the furniture. "I forget my manners, " he said stiffly. "Please, make yourselves comfortable. Robots need not sit if they do not wish to. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I would love to s
it here again, and relax with you, " Dors said, and lowered herself to the small chair beside him. "So many intense memories from this place. I have missed you so!" She could not take her eyes off him.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari smiled down on her. "The worst part is, I was nev
er able to thank you. You gave me so much, and I was never able to say farewell. " His hand patted her shoulder. No gesture, no words, seemed adequate to this occasion. "But then, had you been... organic, I would not have you back with me now, would I? Ho
wever transitory the experience may be. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Suddenly, the deep anger built up for decades came to a head and Hari turned on Daneel, pointed a finger into his chest. "Get this done with! Be done with me! Do your work and make me forget, and leave me in peace! 
Do not torment me with your false flesh and steel bones and immortal thoughts! I am mortal, Daneel. I don't have your strength or your vision!"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You see farther than any other in this room, " Daneel said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "No more! My seeing is over. I was wrong. I'm as blind as any of the quadrillion little points in the equations!"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia backed away as far as she could from this old man with his deep, sharp eyes. Brann stood staring straight ahead, embarrassed, out of his class, out of his place. Klia reached for his hand 
and hugged his arm, to reassure him. Together they stood among the robots and the famous meritocrat, and Klia defied anyone to think them the least of those present. "You were not wrong, " Daneel said. "There is a balance. The Plan is made stronger, but i
t must take some devious routes. I think you will show us how, a few minutes from now. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You overestimate me, Daneel. This young woman\emdash and her companion\emdash and Vara Liso, represent a powerful force I can't fold into the equations. This upwelling of biology...
 " "How do you differ from Vara Liso?" Daneel asked Klia. Brann's nostrils flared and his face darkened. "I'll answer that, " he said. "They're as different as night from day. There isn't a hateful bone in Klia's body\emdash "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I wouldn't go that far, " Klia said, but she was proud of his defense.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I mean it. Vara Liso was a monster!" Brann straightened his neck and thrust out his jaw belligerently, as if daring Daneel to contradict him.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Are you a monster, Klia Asgar?" Hari asked, focusing on her with those deep and discerning eyes.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 She did not turn away. Hari Seldon clearly did not think she was his inferior. There was something beyond respect in his gaze\emdash there was a kind of intellectual terror. "I'm different, " she said.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari smiled wolfishly and shook his head in admiring wonder. "Yes, indeed, you are that. I think Daneel will agree with me that we are done with robots for now, and you are proof of that?"}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I'm very uncomfortable around these robots, " Klia confirmed.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yet you worked with some\emdash did you not? With Lodovik}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
Trema?" Hari turned to Daneel. These suppositions and theories had been perking in his head, subconsciously, for days since the incident in the Hall of Dispensation. Daneel could stop the conscious access of memory, but he could not halt all the de
ep workings of Hari's mind. "He was a robot, wasn't he\emdash Daneel?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes, " Daneel said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "One of yours?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "But\emdash something went wrong. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "He turned against you. Is he still against you?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I am learning, Hari. He has taught me much. Now it is time for you to teach me... once more. Show me what must be done. " Daneel faced Hari.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "What happened to Lodovik in space?" Hari asked.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Daneel explained, then, told Hari all that had happened with the Calvinians, including the end of Plussix and the knowledge of Linge Chen.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "No more secrecy, " Hari mused. "Those who need to know will know, all over the Galaxy. What can I tell you, Daneel? Your work is done. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Not yet, Hari. Not until you find an answer to the problem. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Dors spoke now. "There is a solution, Hari. I know there is\emdash within your equations. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I am not an equation!" Klia shouted. "I am not an aberration or a monster! I just have certain abilities\emdash and so does he!" She pointed to Daneel.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari considered with chin in hand. The itch... So deeply buried, untraceable! He clutched Dors' shoulder, as if to draw strength from her.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "We shed the metal, " he said. "Time to take charge, for ourselves, isn't it, Daneel? And the time will come when psy-chohistory's equations will merge with the equations of all}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 minds, all people. Every individual will be a general example of the whole progress of the people. They will blend.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Young woman, you are not a monster. You are the difficult future. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia stared in puzzlement at Hari. 
"You will have children, and they will have children... stronger than Wanda and Stettin, stronger than the mentalics we have working for us now. Something will happen, something unpredictable, that my equations can't encompass\emdash 
 another and more successful mutation, a stronger Vara Liso. I can't put that into my equations\emdash it is an unknown variable, an individual point-tyranny, all control radiating from one individual!"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari's face had become almost luminous. "You... " He held his hand out to Klia. "Take this hand. Let me feel you. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 She reluctantly reached out.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I need a little nudge, my young friend, " Hari said. "Show me what you are. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Almost without thinking, Klia reached into his mind, saw a brightness there obscured by dark nebulosities, and with a gentle breath of persuasion, another sign of her returning strength, she blew the clouds away.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari gasped and closed his eyes. His head dropped to one shoulder. He was suddenly more than merely tired. He felt a great sense of release, and for the first time 
in decades, a knot in his mind, in his body as well, seemed to untie itself. The brightness in his thoughts was not a way around his errors and the flaws in the equations\emdash it was a deeper understanding of his own irrelevance, in the long term.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 A thousand years from now, he would be a particle in the smooth flow once again, not his own kind of point-tyranny. Dors got up from her chair, taking hold of his arm to help him stay on his feet.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 His work would be forgotten. The Plan would serve its}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 purpose and be swept away, merely one more hypothesis, guiding and shaping, but ultimately no more than another illusion among all the illusions of men\emdash and robots.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 

\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 What he had learned in his time fighting Lamurk for the role of First Minister\emdash that the human race was its own kind of mind, its own self-organizing system, with its own reserved knowledge and tendencies
\emdash }{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Meant that it could also direct its own evolution. Philosophies and theories and truths were morphological appurtenances. Discarded when no longer needed... when the morphology changed.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The robots had served their purpose. Now they would be rejected, shed, by humanity's body social. Psychohistory would be shed as well, when its purpose had been served. And Hari Seldon.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 No man, no woman, no machine, no idea, could reign supreme forever.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari opened his eyes. They were as large as a child's now. He looked around the room, for a moment unable to distinguish people from furniture. Then his vision narrowed and focused.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Thank you, " Hari said. "Daneel was right. " He st
eadied himself against Dors and, with his other hand, braced himself on the back of the chair. It took him some time to order his thoughts. He stared straight at Klia Asgar, and at Brann beyond her.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "My own ego stood before the solution. Your children will
 balance. Your genes and talents will spread. There will be resolution of conflict... and the Plan will continue. But not my Plan. The future will see how wrong I can be.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Your descendants, your many-times great-grandchildren, will correct me. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia had seen deeper into Hari than just the problem he faced. With a little shudder, she stepped forward, and with Dors, they lowered Hari into the chair. "I was never told the}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 truth about you, " she said softly, reaching to touch his cheek. The skin was fine and d
ry and powdery-smooth, faintly resilient, with a ridge of hard bone beneath. Hari smelled clean and human, discipline overlying strength, if such things could be transferred by scent\emdash 
and why not? How could one see that someone had these traits, and not smell them, as well? Old, and frail, and still quite beautiful and strong. "You really are a great man!" she whispered.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "No, my dear, " Hari said. "I am nothing, really. And it is quite wonderful to be nothing, I assure you. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 91.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Better late than never, " Gaal Dornick told the technician as they watched Professor Seldon settle into his chair in the recording booth.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "He seems tired, " the technician said, and checked his gauges to make sure he had the proper settings for the voice of an old man.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
Hari consulted his papers, looking at the first point of major divergence within the equations. He hummed softly to himself, then looked up, waiting for the signal to begin. He was brightly illuminated; the studio beyond was dark, though he 
could see small lights twinkling in the recording booth.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Three spherical lenses descended from above and hovered at a level with his chest. He adjusted the blanket on his legs. Four days ago, he had told his colleagues, and in particular Gaal Dornick, that
 he had had a small stroke, and lost an entire day's recollections. They had bustled about him and insisted that he not strain himself. So he wore this blanket. He could hardly cough without being surrounded by concerned faces.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 It was a small enough lie. And he had mentioned to Gaal that with the stroke had come a calm and peace he had never}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 known before... and a determination to finish his work before Death came finally.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He suspected word would get back to Daneel. Somehow, his old friend and mentor would hear, and approve.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
Hari had felt the subtle workings of Daneel's persuasion, at the conclusion of the meeting with Dors and Klia Asgar and Brann. For a moment, he had felt the memories fading, even as the group headed for the door, and Dors had looked back 
upon him with an almost bitter and passionate regret. And he had felt something else, bright and intense and impulsive, blocking Daneel's effort without the robot knowing.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 It must have come from defiant Klia, stronger than Daneel, naturally resisting the m
anipulations of a robot, however well-meaning. And Hari was grateful. To remember clearly that meeting, and to know what would happen in a year or two... To remember Daneel's promise, delivered in private in Hari's bedroom, while the others waited outside
, old friends having a final chat, that Dors would be with him when her work was done, when his life was nearing its close.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 She could not be with him now. He was too much in the public eye. The return of the Tiger Woman, or someone very like her, was not feasible.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
But there was something else at work here as well. Hari knew that the time of the robots had come to an end, must come to an end; and he knew that it was very likely Daneel would never completely let go of his task. The same eternal concern and dev
otion that Daneel felt for Hari, to so gift him with the return of his great love, would eventually move him to interfere again...}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 So Daneel must be kept in ignorance of some things, a difficult proposition at best.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Together, Wanda, Stettin, Klia, and Brann would see to it, however. Together, they were strong enough and subtle enough.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Could you speak, please, Professor Seldon?" the techni-}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 cian asked from his position in the engineering booth. Gaal Dornick stood beside him, barely visible from where Hari sat.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I am Hari Seldon, old and full of years. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The technician flipped off the voice switch to the studio and looked up at Gaal with some concern. "I hope he's a little more cheerful when we begin in earnest. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You're going to Terminus, aren't you?" Gaal asked the man.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Of course. My family's packed and ready to go. Do you think I'd be here if\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Have you ever met Hari Seldon before now?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Never had the privilege, " the man sniffed. "I've heard tales, of course. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "He knows quite well what he's doing, and what kind of figure to play. Never underestimate him, " Gaal said, and though that was inadequate warning or description, he stopped there, and pointed to the console.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Right, " the technician said, and focused on his equipment. "I'll draw the curtain now and bring in the scramblers. Nobody will know what he's saying besides himself. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 

\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari tapped his finger lightly on the chair arm. The lights on the spheres changed to amber, then to red. He pushed himself up from 
the chair and stared into the darkness beyond, imagining faces, people, men and women, anxious to learn their fates. Well, most of the time, for a few occasions at least, he would be able to help. The devil of it was, he did not know specifically when the
se little speeches would begin to be useless!}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He would record only one message that day, the rest over the next year and a half, as each necessary nudge became clear within the adjusted equations.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 With his most professorial air, quite confident and delib-}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 e
rate, Hari began to speak. He recorded a simple message to those of the Second Foundation, the psychologists and mathists, the mentalics who would train them and alter their germ lines: nothing very profound, merely a kind of pep talk. "To my true grandch
ildren, " he said, "I give my profoundest thanks and wish you luck. You will never need to hear of an impending Seldon Crisis from me... You will never need anything so dramatic, for you know... "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
He had spoken to Wanda the day before, telling her the final part of the puzzle of the Second Foundation. At first, she had been disappointed, vastly; she had so wanted to get away from Trantor, to start fresh on a new world, however barren. But she had h
eld up remarkably well.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
And he had told her that Daneel must never learn of the true whereabouts of the Second Foundation, of the mentalics who could resist all the efforts of the Giskardian robots, should they ever return to take up the reins of secret power.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 A few minutes and he was finished.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He pulled aside the blankets and draped them on the edge of the chair, then stood to leave. The three lenses rose into the darkness above.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Waiting for Gaal to join him, Hari wondered if Death would be a robot. How pro
blematical for a robot it would be to bring both comfort and an end to a human master! He saw a large, smooth, black-skinned robot, infinitely cautious and caring, serving him and driving him to the last.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 The thought made him smile. Would that the universe could ever be so caring and so gentle.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 92.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Dors embraced Klia and Brann, then turned to Lodovik.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I wish I could send a duplicate of myself with you, " she told him, "and experience what you will experience, " she said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Beyond their fenced platform, the small trading ship of Mors Planch, glittering with recent maintenance, rested in its cradle.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You would be most useful to us, " Lodovik said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia looked around the long aisle of ships in the spaceport terminal, and asked, "He isn't coming to see us off?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Hari?" Dors asked, unsure whom she meant.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Daneel, " Klia said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I don't know where he is, now, " Dors said. "He's long had the habit of coming and going without telling anyone what he's up to. His work is done. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I find that hard to believe, " Klia said, and her face reddened. She did not wish to sound like a hypocrite. "I mean... "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Brann nudged her gently with his forearm.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Mors Planch stepped forward. Lodovik still made him uneasy. Well, they would be traveling a great distance together once more. And wh
y should he worry especially about Lodovik, when their ship would cany some fifty humaniform robots, temporarily asleep, and the severed heads of many more? A wealth of fearful riches! And his ticket to freedom, as well. "I was told to confirm our route w
ith you, in case there were last-minute changes. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 He took out a pocket informer and displayed the route to Dors. Four Jumps, over 10, 000 light-years, to Kalgan, a world of pleasure and entertainment for the Galaxy's elite, where they (so the informer said
) would drop off Klia and Brann. Then, thirty-seven individual Jumps, 60, 000 light-years to Eos, where Lodovik would disembark with the robots and the head of Giskard.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Dors studied the travel chart briefly. "Still correct, " she said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Lodovik asked, "Will you be going to Terminus?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "No, " Dors said. "Nor to Star's End, wherever that might be. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You're staying here, " Lodovik surmised.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I am. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia said, "I've read about the Tiger Woman. So hard to believe that was really you. You're staying\emdash for Hari?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I will be here for him at the end. It is my highest and best purpose. I would not be much good for anything else. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Will Daneel let him remember, this time?" Klia asked, and bit her lower lip, nervous at such presumption.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "So it has been promised, " Dors said. "I will have my time with him. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "And until that time?" Lodovik asked, perfectly aware that for humans, this would be a rude and intrusive question.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "That will be for me to decide, " Dors said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Not for Daneel?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Dors regarded him directly, intently.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Do you believe Daneel is finished?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "No, " Dors said quietly.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I cannot believe he is finished, either, or that he is done with you. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "You have your opinions, of course. As any human should. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Lodovik caught the implication, the edge of resentment. "Daneel regards you as human, " Lodovik said. "Does he not?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "He does. Is that an honor, or a curse?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Without waiting for an answer, she turned to go.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Minutes later, from the observation deck looking out over the spaceport, she heard the low rumble and roar of the departing hypership, and looked up briefly to watch its course.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Wanda was none too happy at first to be escorting the young woman and her large mate from the spaceport terminal. Nor was she comfortable about this elaborate deception\emdash 
who, after all, was Grandfather expecting to watch them? Demerzel?}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Nothing had turned out as she hoped, and now to be nursemaid for a potential monster! But Stettin took it all stoically enough, and was well along on striking up a friendship with Brann.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Klia Asgar was another matter. Wanda thought her entirely too moody; but then, so much had changed in the young woman's life in the past week, so many situations had b
een reversed, and she had taken charge in such a fortuitous and insightful way...}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Perhaps there was something essential and useful in Hari's last-minute insight and change of plan. To abandon Star's End and the wonderful difficulties of being pioneers\emdash for 
the inglorious task of hiding out for centuries, and watching the Empire collapse into ruins\emdash 
riding out the Fall of Trantor, the bitter decades; for their children and grandchildren to endure not only endless discipline and training, but the meanest and most horrible centuries in history...}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
Had Grandfather decided all this at the last minute, or had he known all along? Hari Seldon had depths and stratagems it was best not to think about, she decided. Would he manipulate his own granddaughter, keep her in the dark\emdash 
surprise and dismay her?}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Obviously...}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I don't know how to thank you, " Klia said to Wanda as they climbed into the chartered taxi. She adjusted her concealing hood, then attended to Brann's.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "For what?" Wanda asked.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "For putting up with an out-of-control little brat, " Klia said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Wanda could not help but laugh. "Are you reading my mind, dear?" she asked, not sure herself what tone she intended.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "No, " Klia said. "I wouldn't do that. I'm learning. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Aren't we all, " Stettin said, and Wanda looked to her husband with a chastened respect. He had stayed so quiet during her private rants, then had gently and reasonably explained Hari's intricate new Plan.}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I think we'll... learn to rely on each other, very closely, " Wanda said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I'd love that, " Klia said. Her eyes glittered under the hood, and Wanda realized that they were filled with tears. She could feel the wash of need from the young woman\emdash 
still little more than a girl, actually!}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 And how would that be\emdash to have this mentalic female start regarding her as a mother]}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 She reached out and took Klia's hand. "Not that it will be easy, " she said. "But... we'll win, in the end. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Of course, " Klia said, her voice trembling. "That's what Hari\emdash what Professor Seldon plans. I look forward so much to learning from you. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Their children and grandchildren would twine their genes, and the psychologists of the Second Foundation could study and come to understand persuasion\emdash could utilize it more efficie
ntly. By breeding and by research, they would be creating a race that would withstand centuries of adversity, and rise to conquer... secretly, quietly.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 An anodyne against unexpected mutations, hidden far from the First Foundation, and away from the robots.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 And how in sky would she explain this to the psychologists, the mathists, who had already fought against the inclusion of the mentalics?}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 They will help keep us secret during the hard times to come. Well, maybe she was up to the task of reconciling all these disparate talents. She had better be.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 If Grandfather was right, the two most important human beings in the Galaxy were now in Wanda's care. Wanda turned away from Klia, her own eyes moist, and caught a look from Brann in the seat opposite. Slow, large, 
with secret depths, the burly Dahlite nodded solemnly and peered out the semisilvered window.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I'm very confused, " Mors Planch said as the acceleration eased and the ship's artificial gravity came into play. "Who's}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 deceiving whom? How can you believe Daneel won't find out? How do you know he didn't plan for the youngsters to stay here all along?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "It is not my concern, " Lodovik said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Will you tell him, on Eos?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "No, " Lodovik said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Won't he just know?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "He will not learn from me, " Lodovik said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Why not?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
Lodovik smiled, and said no more. Then, within his positronic pathways, the requested blankness of certain knowledge began to build. The forgetfulness of Klia Asgar would soon envelop him. New memories would come into play, of arriving on bright, gay K
algan and putting the two young humans into the charge of agents of the future Second Foundation. He would become part of a false trail, to deceive any who might come after them.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 At the last, he had followed his insight, his newfound instinct, provoked by Voltaire, to the letter. And if Daneel does know\emdash then he will not oppose what is set in place, because he trusts the instincts of}{
\fs20  }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Hari Seldon.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Well, it's just you and me, old friend, " Mors said with an edge in his voice. "What should we talk about this time?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 EPILOGUE}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I have been dreaming, perhaps, " Joan said.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Me, too, " Voltaire said. "What did you dream of?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Very painful things. Of an arrow in my neck and a brick striking my head. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Your historical traumas, before the flames. I myself dreamed of dying, " Voltaire said. "Are you together yet?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Not yet. Not all of the backups have located our new centers. She nearly destroyed us!" Joan said angrily.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "She was made to destroy us, " Voltaire said. "To her very core, she despised all minds not human. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "But\emdash " A momentary panic. "You say she despised... "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Yes. She is dead now. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "What of the others, the children who were working with the Cafainians\emdash the ones you were helping?" Joan asked.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "They have left Trantor, last I heard. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Has it all been resolved, then?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Our argument, my dearest, or\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Don't call me that, you godless\emdash "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Shhh, " Voltaire attempted to soothe, with no success.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "The voices te}{\fs20 ll }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 me}{\fs20  }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 l have been seduced by a master, a master Ear. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Who can argue with such revelations? Let us decide to disagree, even should it be forever, " Voltaire said. "I will say I did not feel comfortable apart from you. Encoded in the warps}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 and weft of space, imposed upon plasmas and fields of energy like a spider riding a web, I wandered with the wraiths,
 supped on their diffuse energy feasts, observed their decadent societies, mated and danced... How like the ancien regime it all was, yet bloodless, predictable, angelic! I missed the perversity, the femininity, the humanity. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "How flattering, that you miss my perversity. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
"In boredom I followed the trails of human ships, and came upon a vessel in distress, tossed by the storm of a dying star. And within, I found a mechanical human being, weakened by circumstance, besieged by particles my hosts had taught
 me to regard as very tasty... A marvelous opportunity!"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "A chance for you to interfere with a vulnerable spirit. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Spirit? Perhaps... So much unexpressed need for approval, for fulfillment. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Like a child, for you to bend and distort. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I found a seed 
of freedom, very subtle. I merely watered it with a retunneled electron or two, a positronic pathway shunted from here to here... I helped the particles do what they might have done anyway, had he broken his programmed chains. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "A devil's sleight of handlessness, " Joan said, but not without some admiration. "You have always been clever that way. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I did nothing a good God would not approve of. I allowed free will to blossom. Do not be harsh with me, Maid. I will be civil, if you allow me my foibles. Perhaps it is more interesting that way. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I hardly worry about your sins anymore, " Joan said. "After what happened, when that horrible woman... " The equivalent of a shudder. "I fear we may both face dissolution again\emdash 
the loss of our very souls. After all, we are not human... "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
Voltaire interrupted this line of reasoning, which still disturbed him. "Nobody knows we are here. We were blown apart; they felt us die. They have their own concerns now. We are irrelevant ghosts who never truly lived. But if robots 
can become human... Then why not we, my love? We will not haunt the Mesh forever. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Joan absorbed this without replying for several millionths of a second. Then, in their deeply buried matrix, concealed in the depths of a machine designed to keep constant 
track of the daily accumulation of wealth on Trantor, she felt the last segments of her stored self rejoin with the hastily saved fragments of her last moments with Daneel in the Hall of Dispensation.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "There, " she said. "I am together. I say again, what of those issues unresolved\emdash the decidability of the fate of humankind, the success of the blessed Hari Seldon?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 

\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "The larger issues appear to be in flux once more, " Voltaire said dryly.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "No final judgments?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Do you mean the judgment of the vast Nobodaddy, the Nothing Father of your delusions, or the mechanical man you have lusted after these past scores of years?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 Joan dismissed the tone and the implications with a precise iciness. "God speaks through our deeds, and, of course, through me. Whatever my origins, I maintain the pattern of His Voice. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Of course. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Daneel... "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Determines nothing, and is lost without humanity. "}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "No outcome, then, " she said, disappointed.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "Are you afraid of how it will all turn out, my dear?" Voltaire asked.}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "I am afraid of not being there when it is resolved. These strong-minded children... If they learned of us, they would hate us, perhaps strive to destroy us for good!"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "They have other concerns, and will never know about us, " Voltaire said. "They have a great deception to play. I have been investigating while you yet knitted your selves together. "}{
\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
\par }{\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 "And what did you learn?"}{\f1\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033 
